title: saucepan cookies
directions: Pour melted shortening over brown sugar and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 17 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and remove from pan when cold.

title: glaze for fresh apple cake
directions: Cook until thick enough to dribble over cake.

title: english pea salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in medium bowl.
Chill before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole; add onion and garlic.
Microwave (High) 5 to 6 minutes or until set; stir once.
Stir to break meat into small pieces; drain.
Stir in tomato paste, water, green chilies, olives and salt.
Cover with lid.
Microwave (High) for 9 to 10 minutes or until flavors are blended and sauce is bubbly, stirring twice.
Set aside.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Salt chicken.
Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Cut in chunks.
Mix melted margarine, cracker crumbs and poppy seed. Pat 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Layer chicken on top of crumb mixture.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with cherry pie filling.
Ready to serve.
Excellent with coffee.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fresh vegetable bake
directions: Combine veggies and spoon into 4-quart casserole.
In small saucepan, combine broth and herbs.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Bring to a boil the squash, onion and water. Cover and simmer until tender.
While this is cooking mix cornbread crumbs, cream of chicken soup, margarine and black pepper.
Mix with squash mixture and bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french cheeseburger
directions: Slice the bread lengthwise and hull out loaf (top and bottom). Brown hamburger and onions, then add catsup.
Spoon into bottom part of the bread.
Put a slice of cheese on top of meat.
Place top of bread on sandwich, then roll in plastic wrap.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Slice and serve with salad.

title: "the best" yeast bread
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Heat milk to lukewarm. Add yeast, stirring to dissolve.
Cream 1 stick butter, sugar and salt.
Add milk and yeast to butter mixture.
Beat eggs and add. Beat together.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, mixing well.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over mix.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Slice to serve.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Combine all other ingredients in large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: bacon-onion cheese balls
directions: Fry bacon; cool and crumble.
Mix softened cream cheese, salad dressing, cheese, bacon bits and onion.
When well mixed, form into ball and chill.
Ball may be rolled in finely chopped walnuts or pecans or parsley flakes.

title: mock hollandaise sauce
directions: Blend ingredients; refrigerate if desired.
Heat over hot water before serving.
Yields about 1 cup sauce.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
If desired, add 2 cups of sliced bananas at serving time.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening together.
Then add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add rest of ingredients and beat good.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Slice 1/2 stick butter over Veg-All, Cheez Whiz and salt and pepper.
Crumble crackers and put over mixture.
Add other 1/2 stick butter.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: prime rib roast beef
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with 3 cups water.
Put frozen roast in crock-pot.
Pour liquid mixture over it.
Put lid on and cook on low overnight.
Serve.
Cut in thin slices on Kaiser buns.
Use juice to dip sandwich in.

title: mom's million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; bring to full rolling boil.
Boil and stir for 4 1/2 minutes.
Break up chocolate and mix with other ingredients.
Pour hot syrup over all ingredients and stir.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: christmas ruby red salad(good anytime)
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions.
Add pineapple juice. Chill and serve.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix coconut, milk, sugar and butter together.
Spread in a sheet cake or cookie pan.
Put in freezer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove; cut into bars.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip bars into chocolate mixture (I dip them with a toothpick).
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: barbecue scalloped potatoes
directions: Turn on oven and set at 350° (moderate).
Mix first 7 ingredients in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir in potatoes until well mixed. Put mixture into a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese and paprika over top.
Bake near center of oven about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: ranch cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet (for smaller cookie, use teaspoon).
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: campfire macaroni
directions: Brown and drain meat; add onion.
Cook until clear.
Add remaining ingredients except beans and cheese.
Cook until macaroni is tender.
Add beans and cheese.
Cook until heated through and serve warm.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Dice tomatoes, green pepper, cheese and ham.
Cook spaghetti; drain and cool with cold water.
Toss together.
Add Italian dressing.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Chill until firm.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: banana dream pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip with 1 cup of milk as directed on package, using a large mixer bowl.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl. Spoon into pie crust. Chill for 4 hours.

title: frosted graham crackers
directions: Fill an 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with graham crackers.
Boil 1 cup butter and 1 cup brown sugar for a few minutes.
Add 1/2 cup ground nuts to mixture.
Pour over graham crackers and spread evenly.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, turning and mixing every 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool slightly, then add raisins and any other dry fruit you like.
Store in an airtight container.

title: crab cakes
directions: Clean crab meat and pick out all bones.
Combine everything and roll in egg, then bread crumbs and fry in deep fat.

title: hawaiian cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy; stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve on crackers or bread.
Yield:
3 1/4 cups.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until thick; sift the remaining dry ingredients together. Fold in the dates or raisins and nuts; pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wood pick comes out clean.
Makes two loaves.

title: special potato dish
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican soup
directions: Cook ground meat until browned.
Drain and add taco seasoning, stirring well. Add tomato sauce and chopped tomatoes.
Stir in corn and simmer over low heat 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Use enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out on floured bread board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown. Will be soft.

title: mozzarella munchies
directions: Mix the cheese, onion and Miracle Whip together and spread on party rye.
Put under the boiler to slightly brown and bubbly. Serve.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli only until it separates.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Alternate first broccoli, then mixture.
Repeat.
Crush Ritz crackers over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Pour broccoli back into pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese and 1/2 stick of margarine until melted.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Melt remaining margarine in pan and stir in crushed Ritz crackers, then spread over the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: cherry pie(makes 10 pies.)
directions: Combine sugar, tapioca, salt and almond flavor.
Mix thoroughly with fruit and fruit juices before pouring into shells. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: arkansas beans
directions: Fry hamburger meat in large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Pour pork and beans in with hamburger meat, then barbecue sauce.
Heat thoroughly.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice until tender in salted water.
Mix all ingredients. Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup diced Cheddar cheese.
Pour into flat bakeware.
Top with cooking cheese.
Brown cheese in hot oven.
Serve.

title: sauteed zucchini
directions: Heat skillet.
Put in oil.
Heat and put in garlic, zucchini, salt and pepper. Cook few minutes until tender.
Great taste.

title: squash bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour the mixture into a greased skillet. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream
oleo,
powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Put in refrigerator to chill;
roll in balls. Bake
at 400° until done.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar. Cool.
Roll in plain sugar.

title: barley with ham
directions: Simmer ham in water until ham loosens from bone.
Discard bone and fat.
Add barley and onion.
Cook until barley is tender, about 1 hour.
Serves 2 as a main course.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and add sugar.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in 1 pint warm water and let set until it gets thick as honey.
Add all cranberries, nuts, celery, marshmallows, apples and pineapple.
Add one big cup of Cool Whip. Put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.

title: n.d. sugar cookies
directions: Cream together all moist ingredients.
Sift together and add all dry ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Dip in sugar. Flatten with fork.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes or until very light brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add beaten egg, then molasses, vinegar and cold water.
Sift flour, soda and ginger and add to first mixture.
Stir in as much of the flour as you can and knead in remainder.
Roll out.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into small squares.
Drop into hot liquid.
Cover closely and cook 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix all ingredients excluding confectioners sugar and bring to a boil.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar.
Add about 1/3 at a time, and use an electric mixer for beating.
Add vanilla and continue mixing until mixture is of spreading consistency.
Add chopped nuts if desired.

title: cream cheese chocolate chip bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cookie pan and preheat oven to 350°. Prepare Toll House cookie dough as directed on package of chocolate chips.
Place 3/4 of dough on bottom of pan.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and beaten eggs.
Pour over top of dough in pan. Glob on the rest of the dough.
Bake for 30 minutes and touch to see if dough springs back.
May need to bake for 40 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix hot water and yeast until dissolved.
Stir warm water and brown sugar.
Slowly add flour.
Mix until smooth.
Roll dough until smooth and 16-inches for each pretzel.
Twist into shape.

title: mango-kiwi salsa
directions: Dice fruit and vegetables. Add other ingredients and chill before serving. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp and asparagus casserole
directions: Blanch asparagus for three minutes in small saucepan.
Melt butter and stir in flour.
Cook, stirring, for one minute. Gradually add cream or half and half and milk.
Cook until thick. Stir in white wine, cream or chicken broth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in egg yolk, cheese and shrimp.
Put in buttered casserole dish layered: one half asparagus, then one half shrimp. Repeat layer and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fast strawberry mousse
directions: Chop walnuts and mix with sugar and spices.
Grease an 11 x 16-inch pan with melted butter.
Place 4 filo in pan, brushing each with melted butter.
Sprinkle with thin layer of nut mixture. Cover with 3 filo, brushing each with melted butter.
Continue this procedure until all filo and mixture is used.
Finish with 4 filo on top, brushing each with butter.
Cut into about 75 small squares (before baking).
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour or longer, until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and cool.
Pour warm syrup over pastry.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil 10 minutes and remove from heat to cool dark place.
Let stand 3 days, stirring 3 or 4 times each day. Can cold in sterilized jars.
Seal.
The berries remain whole and the juice is thick.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: lime jello salad
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan, add water, lime Jell-O and cream cheese. Heat on medium heat until cream cheese melts.
After cheese melts, add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Then refrigerate until its almost firm.
Then add pineapple juice, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Pour into bowl. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Work in butter until it disappears.
Add eggs and vanilla and knead until soft and pliable.
Pinch off piece of dough and roll into length of about 4 to 5-inches, twist and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown lamb and onion.
Add beans, ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a large casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuits for your dog
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well, roll out and cut with "bone" shaped cookie cutter.
Bake at 300° until very hard.
Fido will love these!

title: cowboy's delight(pineapple dessert)
directions: Mix together the vanilla wafers and 1/4 cup melted butter and pack into an 8 x 8-inch dessert dish.
Cream the powdered sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Add eggs and beat 10 minutes.
Beat whipping cream until stiff (could use Cool Whip).
Add drained crushed pineapple and nuts (if desired).
Mix the sugar, butter and egg mixture.
Top with pineapple mixture.
Decorate with vanilla wafer crumbs, whipping cream, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: chicken fried steaks
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; sprinkle on both sides of steaks.
Combine egg and milk in a shallow bowl.
Dip steaks in egg mixture, then dredge in cracker crumbs.
Pour oil to depth of 1/2 inch into large, heavy skillet.
Fry steaks in hot oil over medium heat until brown, turning once.
Remove steaks; drain off drippings, reserving 3 tablespoons.
In skillet, add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Add broth and 1/2 cup milk; stir constantly until thick.
Add Worcestershire sauce; stir.
Serve gravy with steaks and cooked rice or mashed potatoes.

title: mexican cornbread with ground beef
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, salt, bacon drippings, eggs, soda and corn in mixing bowl. Set aside. Saute ground beef in skillet. Drain on paper towels. Grease a large black iron skillet and heat. Sprinkle bottom with a thin layer of cornmeal and brown slightly. Pour half of the batter in hot skillet.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter, then sprinkle on the meat, onion and peppers.
Pour remaining batter on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.
Serve with a tossed green salad, iced tea and fruit dessert for a complete meal.

title: barbecued hamburger-bean casserole
directions: Cook hamburger with onion until brown, then drain.
Stir in brown sugar, salt, barbecue sauce and pork and beans and heat through.
Place in casserole.
Separate biscuits and cut in half. Sprinkle with cheese, then arrange over hamburger mixture.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until biscuits are brown.

title: sarah matt's onion soup
directions: Place butter and one "plop" of oil in a large kettle.
Cut up onions and saute in kettle.
Add salt as desired and 1 spoon sugar for flavor and browning.
When onions are soft and brown, sprinkle 2 spoonfuls (1 at a time) of flour and mix into onions.
It will be pasty.
Add meat and brown, about 30 minutes.
Add 4 cans of broth and 4 cans of water.
Add 3 to 4 bay leaves and a few sprinkles of red pepper.
Bring mix to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer for as long as you would like.
Serve in bowls with torn pieces of bread and cheese, letting the cheese melt.
Enjoy!

title: special white rolls
directions: Mix
1 1/2 cups flour, salt, sugar, sour cream and milk in mixer
at
medium
speed until blended.
Dissolve yeast in warm water
and add it along with the melted margarine to the flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Remove from mixer and beat with spoon, gradually adding the remaining flour.
If dough is too sticky
to
handle, add a little more flour and knead for several minutes.
Place
dough in a large pan in a warm place and let rise until doubled in size.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, tomatoes and eggs; set aside.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: irish champ
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Just cover with salted water and boil until tender.

title: banana oatmeal drops
directions: *Use less sugar if using sweetened coconut.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Boil tapioca, water and salt for 1/2 hour.
Two hours later, add jello and sugar.
When cool, top with whipped cream and fruit. Mix in marshmallows.

title: crumb cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy. Add sugar and beat.
Mix baking powder and graham cracker crumbs. Then add to mixture.
Add vanilla and then the nuts.
Pour into 2 layer cake pans.
Bake at 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chestnut and cranberry dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2 1/4-3 qt. baking dish.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, warm stock until steam begins to rise, 3-5 minutes.
Remove from heat, and add cranberries; set aside.
In a large fry pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add onion, celery, and carrot; saute, stirring , until tender and translucent, 2-3 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer to a bowl.
In the same pan, saute sausage, stirring and crumbling with a fork, until lightly browned and cooked through, about 10 minutes. Transfer sausage to bowl with vegetables.
In a large bowl, stir egg white slowly pouring in stock and cranberries.
Add bread and stir until well blended.
Let stand, stirring occasionally, until stock is absorbed, 6-8 minutes.
Add vegetable-sausage mixture, chestnuts, sage, thyme, and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper and stir to mix well.
Transfer to prepared baking dish.
Bake until brown and crispy, 45-50 minutes.
Serves 10-12.

title: sailboat salad
directions: Wash lettuce leaves and stack on four salad plates.
Cut the cantaloupe in half and scoop out the seeds.
Cut each half into half.
Place each piece in the "green sea" of lettuce.
Cut the 2 slices of cheese in half diagonally (from corner to corner).
Use a toothpick and make a sail with the cheese and then "raise the sail" on each "boat".

title: walt and roberta's favorite seven layer cookies or hello dollys
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over melted butter, then spread crumbs with chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips.
Sprinkle coconut over this, followed by the milk poured evenly over the coconut and add the chopped pecans on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: low-fat scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; layer in baking dish with flour and salt and pepper.
Cover with canned milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: kathy's breakfast casserole
directions: Salt and pepper lightly.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Put bread, sausage and cheese into pan.
Pour egg mixture (beat eggs, 2 1/4 cups milk and mustard) into pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Blend flour, cinnamon and butter with pastry blender. Sprinkle over apples in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with ice cream.

title: cheese cake
directions: For 9-inch pie pan, prepare Dream Whip as on package, using vanilla and cold milk.
When topping peaks with blender, add cream cheese, slowly blending.
Add sugar and blend.
Pour into crust. Chill about 3 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: banana loaf
directions: Crush bananas in large bowl.
Mix in all other ingredients. Pour into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out clean.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger in
1 tablespoon fat.
Add other ingredients. Cover and
simmer
for
30	minutes.
Add more tomato juice if it is too dry.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Top with lemon topping. Chill 3 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: self crust egg custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add to well-beaten eggs.
Add milk, evaporated milk, melted butter, salt and vanilla flavoring and mix well.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan with butter; pour mixture in pan and sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken appetizers
directions: Mix soup, dressing and preserves in bowl.
Put chicken in a 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Cover with mixture.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients together.
After combined, place uncooked chicken on top of rice mixture.
Spoon soup over the top of the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until rice is cooked.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place drained pineapple in baking dish.
Mix flour with sugar and sprinkle over pineapple.
Cover with cheese and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Cut margarine into small pieces and place on top of crackers.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: main dish salad
directions: Make tossed salad.
Cut up egg and cheese in salad or add cottage cheese to salad.
Add dressing.
Serves 1.

title: herbed halibut
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, green onions, parsley, basil and cloves in a bowl.
Stir in melted margarine.
Brush four 12-inch foil squares lightly with oil.
Place 1 fish steak on each square.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with crumbs.
Spoon wine around each steak.
Seal foil securely.
Place packets on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Makes 4 servings.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Serve with assorted raw veggies.

title: barbecue country style spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs in heavy skillet.
While ribs are browning, make a sauce from remaining ingredients.
Cook all for 10 minutes. Pour over ribs and cook for 2 hours in a 375° oven.
Remove; cover the last half hour to glaze them.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together; form into small balls.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool on wire racks.

title: washington favorite senate bean soup
directions: Put beans in a large pot.
Add the 2 or better quarts of water and soak overnight.
Next day, drain the beans and add more water, more than cover.
Add the ham bone to the beans and water, cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove the ham bone from pot and chop the meat and return it to the pot.
Then add onion, potato, celery and garlic.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Be sure there is enough water, cook for another hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to oil, then add eggs, pumpkin, spices (sifted together with flour), water and nuts.
Bake one hour at 350°. Makes 1 large or two small loaves.

title: black-eyed bean salad
directions: Prepare rice and limas as labels direct. Drain black-eyed peas. Dice red pepper. In large bowl, mix peas, red pepper, parsley, lemon juice, oil, mustard, sugar and salt. Add rice and limas. Chill.

title: "maybe governor of texas" chili
directions: *Favorite meat is to use
ground
moose,
if not available, use ground beef round.
Venison
is
good to mix in with beef and also you can add ground
pork.
You need a total of 6 pounds of meat with the sauteed onion.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat milk, sour cream and pudding mix until smooth.
Place 1/3 sliced bananas into pastry shell.
Top with 1/2 pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Arrange the remaining bananas on top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: company chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Spread rice on bottom of greased 3-quart casserole.
Layer with mushrooms, then chicken.
Mix undiluted soups with savory and dry soup mix.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Pour broth around sides to moisten rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sassy cinnamon muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine egg, milk and oil. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour and salt.
Brown in oil for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Reserve 1/4 cup pan juice.
In pan, stir honey, teriyaki sauce, chives, pepper and juice; heat to boiling.
Boil for 30 seconds.
Add pineapple; heat again.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: meatball porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly meat, rice, 1/3 cup water, onion, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape into well rounded tablespoon sized meatballs; place in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover pan with foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve with pasta if desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Tear small pieces of dough off, dip in melted butter, then in sugar mixture.
Drop into Bundt cake pan.
Let raise to within 1 inch of top of pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ranch and cheddar bread
directions: Spread each cut side with Ranch dressing. Add cheese and broil until lightly browned. Garnish with parsley.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan. When done, remove from oven and prick with fork.
Prepare gelatin as on box, then pour over cake.
Prepare pudding and spread over cake.
Put glaze over pudding.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Slice strawberries and place on top.

title: cinnamon rolls "ready in the morning"
directions: At 4 p.m., boil first 4 ingredients together.
Set in sink in water to cool.
In a big bowl, dissolve the yeast in water.
Stir in cooled mixture, 2 beaten eggs and enough flour to handle easily.
Put in a greased bowl and let rise.
At 9 to 10 p.m., punch down.
Roll out in rectangle; spread with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon (3 tablespoons cinnamon, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup brown sugar).
Roll up and cut.
Makes about 40 if cut about 1-inch.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake according to directions.
Just before baking, add red food coloring and stir into cake.
Bake according to directions.
Combine egg whites, sugar and strawberries in top of double boiler; beat with mixer to mix.
Place over rapidly boiling water; beat constantly with mixer.
Cook 7 minutes, or until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from boiling water; beat until cool.
Fold in 2/3 cup strawberries.
Spread over cake.

title: garlic pork roast
directions: With a sharp knife, cut deep pockets between each rib on meaty side of roast.
Combine green peppers, green onion, celery and garlic; stuff deeply into pockets.
Season roast with salt and cayenne pepper.
Insert meat thermometer.
Place roast, rib side down, in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 to 3 hours or until thermometer reads 170°.
Let stand 15 minutes before carving.

title: hershey easy pie
directions: Chop each peanut butter cup into 6 pieces, set aside. Microwave kisses in medium microwave safe bowl on high 1 minute or just until chocolate is melted when stirred, stir in 3 1/2 c. whipped topping until blended.
Spread half of chocolate mixture into crust, sprinkle with peanut better cup pieces.
Top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.

title: red velvet cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and food color; blend.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Stir baking soda into vinegar; fold carefully into batter (do not beat).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg yolks.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to butter, sugar, egg mixture alternately with the milk and flavoring.
Beat well.
Carefully fold in egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan or
in 2 loaf pans.
Pans should be greased and floured.
Bake in a 375° oven until done.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half
of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat.
Pour caramel mixture over baked cake.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the nuts and all of chocolate chips over mixture.
Pour remaining batter over this. Sprinkle with rest of the nuts and bake 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge(small batch, can be doubled)
directions: Remove from heat and add 1/2 stick butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let cool to 135°.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered dish.
It should be getting stiff as you mix it up. It does not take long to set up.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar and Karo well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in 1 teaspoon oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add bouillon cube with 1 cup hot water, then add stewed tomatoes and green pepper.
Cook 30 minutes, then add cornstarch and soya sauce.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: chili beans
directions: Put meat in shortening, then add chopped onion and garlic. Next, add the kidney beans, tomato soup and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Just before serving, top with cheese and place under the broiler to melt cheese.

title: macaroni cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Grate block cheese in bowl.
Mix powdered cheese, milk and eggs together.
Layer macaroni, then cheese alternately in casserole dish.
Pour mixture on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 450° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Mix all together and cook over medium heat until tender.
If cabbage seems to be quite moist, cut water by 1/2 cup.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and rind.
Blend in condensed milk.
Beat egg yolks slightly; blend into mixture.
Pour into cooled pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each. Continue beating until very stiff peaks form.
Pile lightly on pie filling.
Brown in oven (350°) for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: jollof rice
directions: Brown beef in 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven.
Drain.
Add chicken, broth, mushrooms, rice, onion, green pepper, barbecue sauce and seasoning; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add tomatoes; mix lightly.

title: spanish rice(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water until tender. Fry 1/2 cup bacon until crisp. Add onion and green pepper; simmer until onion is soft and yellow. Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour rice into strainer and rinse with hot running water. Add rice to onions, bacon and green pepper mixture. Mix well and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: praline pumpkin bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and butter; pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry slush
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the cranberries and 1 1/2 cups water over medium heat until the berries pop, about 15 minutes. Stir in raspberries. Transfer to a blender or food processor; cover and process until smooth. Strain and discard seeds, reserving juice. Pour the juice into a 2-quart freezer-proof container; set aside. In a small
saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over remaining water. Let stand for 1 minute. Stir in sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved. Add to berry juice. Stir in ginger ale; cover and freeze.

title: ma hettie's pound cake
directions: Crem the butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Alternately add 1 cup milk and flour mixture.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil over medium heat, add onion and cook until soft, about 6 minutes.
Stir garlic and bell pepper and saute 2 minutes. Blend in flour; add tomato sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in water, thyme, parsley and shrimp.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken noodle dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone.
Add 2 cans cream of chicken soup to broth.
Add noodle dumplings.
Cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: open-faced chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken and celery.
Mix salt, onion, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Mix into chicken.
Split buns.
Place, cut side down, on broiler rack.
Brown lightly. Turn and butter cut side. Spread each with 1/4 cup chicken mixture. Toss cheese and corn chips together.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Broil 3-inches from heat until cheese is melted and slightly browned.
Place on tray; garnish.

title: sauteed vegetable medley
directions: The goal here is to create a variety of shapes, colors and tastes.
It is not important to do it exactly as I do, but to find what you and your family like.
I will describe how I do it.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Mix eggs, dry mustard, salt and milk.
Layer bread, cheese and chicken in order listed.
Pour liquid mixture over bread layers. Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, mix 1/3 to 1/2 cup melted butter with 2 1/2 cups corn flakes.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: turkey goulash
directions: Combine turkey, seasonings, tomatoes, juice, green pepper, onion flakes, sweetener and mushrooms with liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and continue to boil, uncovered, until macaroni absorbs all of the juice and is tender, about 20 minutes. Divide evenly.
Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, eggs, 1/2 cup Romano, salt, pepper and Accent until well combined.

title: skillet sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan; add sliced meats.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes, stirring until brown.
Add broth and stir 30 seconds. Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly to mix.
Cover and simmer over moderately low heat 10 minutes, until hot and flavors blend.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.
Contains 311 calories.

title: icebox cake
directions: Save the vanilla wafer box.
Put all ingredients together and put in the box you saved; place in refrigerator.
Cool for 24 hours.
Tear box away and serve.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Slice off top of loaf of bread and carve out center (keep). Brown and drain ground beef, sausage, onion and bell pepper. Combine egg, milk and bread (center).
Add to meat.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on bottom of bread.
Add meat mixture on top of cheese.
Add cubes of Velveeta on top of meat.
Put on top loaf. Brush with butter.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Do not overbake.
Take out of foil and slice.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In a saucepan, over medium heat, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup and cream cheese cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and hot.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges or shred and cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
For sauce, melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat; stir until smooth.
Stir in milk; boil for 1 minute until thick.
Spread sauce over cabbage.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, the baking powder and salt into bowl.
Blend in milk and shortening; stir in nuts.
Pour into ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.

title: mexican hash
directions: Cook and stir beef, onion, garlic and crushed red pepper in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown. Drain. Add tomatoes, green pepper, raisins, salt, chili powder, cumin, cloves and cinnamon. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
In separate pan, cook and stir almonds over medium heat until golden, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir almonds and olives into beef mixture. Serve with rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in greased casserole dish.
Place cheese over chicken breast.
Spread soup and sour cream over cheese.
Top with crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: schnitzel
directions: Beat each chop with meat beater until about 1/4-inch thick. Add Season-All.
Beat eggs with fork on a flat plate.
Put breadcrumbs on another plate.
Put seasoned chops first in eggs to coat on both sides and then in breadcrumbs.
Put breaded chops in medium hot grease in frying pan and brown both sides for 5 to 7 minutes, turning each chop only once.
Enjoy.

title: chef tony lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Cook beef, garlic and onions in large saucepan for 10 minutes.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix well and let simmer 15 minutes.
In bowl, combine cottage cheese and eggs.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan.
Arrange several alternate layers of cooked and drained lasagna, sliced cheese, meat sauce and cottage cheese mixture, beginning with lasagna and ending with meat sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, water, pudding mix, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Fill and frost with Coconut-Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Filling will be soft but will set while cooling.
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: best homemade chili
directions: In a large Dutch oven or soup kettle, brown beef with onions; drain. Stir in spices and tomato sauce. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Combine flour and vinegar. Stir into chili. Simmer another 15 minutes or until thickened.

title: hot dog and potato casserole
directions: Place layer of half potatoes and onions and half of the hot dogs over bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle half the margarine.
Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat, using remaining ingredients.
Pour warm milk over casserole.

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and strain and return to pan.
Add sauce and water, bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. In 9 x 13-inch pan add meat sauce, noodles and cottage cheese. Repeat in layers, ending in layer of cheese.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix the chiles, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and green onions.
Coat tortillas in soup mixture.
Place one layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken layer and cheese, then repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter, soda and sugar. Add as much flour as can be rolled in. Knead well. Cut in squares. Bake at 350 until done.

title: sugar cookies(early 1900's recipe)
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add liquids and mix well. Roll out dough 1/8 inch thick and cut in desired shape.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 7 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat in oven until melted.

title: country corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish sprayed with Pam for approximately 45 minutes. Add the Cheddar cheese on top after half done.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add all but brown sugar and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top the brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Bake Angel Loaves.
Cool.
Cut cake crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut each slice in half and put together with matching slice of cherry-nut or vanilla ice cream.
If desired, top with chocolate sauce.
Makes 12 to 14 sandwiches.
Use remaining loaf for another dessert.

title: our famous chili
directions: Drain beans before adding to pot.
Put all ingredients into a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or if using high, cook 6 to 8 hours.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together with electric mixer. Blend into the Cool Whip.
Pour into the graham cracker crusts. Top with chopped nuts.
Makes 2 pies or 1 (9 x 13-inch) loaf.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; add broth, soy sauce and sugar.
Add vegetables; bring to a full boil, separating vegetables with fork, stirring frequently until sauce and cubes are blended.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Bring to a boil again. Stir in rice and remove from heat; let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients, except corn and soda, for 5 minutes, mixing well and stirring.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir in quickly.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Put in 2 large, flat pans and place in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Be sure to stir 2 or 3 times.
Store in lightly closed container.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan (or may use small cookie sheet that has deep sides). Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on bottom of pan.
Then pour batter over the coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Done when pick comes out clean.
Cool, then frost with thin icing (drizzle on).

title: chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 9 to 10 1/2 minutes.
Add chocolate bits and marshmallow cream.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate pieces are melted.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bubble recipe
directions: Combine, shake and let settle 4 hours.
Have fun with bubble wand.
Do not eat.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix thoroughly all the ingredients.
Pour into prepared oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Saute onion in margarine and cool. Add sour cream, salt, dill weed and half of cheese. Mix muffin mix with corn, egg and milk. Pour in 13 x 9-inch cake pan, then onion mixture, then top with last half of shredded cheese. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ham roll ups
directions: Blend cheeses and margarine.
Spread 1/4-inch on each slice of ham.
Roll up; chill several hours or wrap and freeze.

title: e-z pizza
directions: Chop bell pepper and green onion together, sprinkle over sauce. Add sausage, pepperoni or hamburger.
Top with cheese.
Cook about 10 minutes or until cheese begins to brown.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Grate together cucumber, carrots and onion.
Drain the juice and save.
Cream together the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Heat juice till hot, but not boiling, let it cool in cold water, add pkg. of knox gelation and stir together, let cool again until room temperature.
Mix cucumber mix, and cream cheese mix into juice mixture.
Stir well, and then beat mixture until it is fluffy and creamy.
Refrigerate over night, salt to taste and spread onto frozen bread, trim off crust of bread and cut into finger sandwiches.

title: currant glazed appetizer franks
directions: Heat jelly and mustard together; stir occasionally, until blended.
Add franks and heat.
Serve with toothpicks.
Use a fondue pan which keeps just the right heat but does not burn.

title: franklin pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add 3 cups of flour mixture.
Pour last cup of flour over fruits and pecans.
Add this to other ingredients.
Add flavoring, mix well.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour cake in pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes and grate or mash with a wire potato masher. Combine cheese and butter.
Melt.
Add sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Fold in potatoes.
Put into 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Yummy.

title: fruit bread
directions: Blend together the butter and sugar and beat.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda and add to butter mixture.
Add beaten egg and gradually add buttermilk.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt gin's pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and butter and add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the creamed mixture to the flour mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, depending on oven.

title: russian tea(old recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put 4 to 5 teaspoons in cup of hot water.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In small saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil 2 minutes until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and chives; stir until cheese is melted.
Arrange potato slices in prepared baking dish. Spoon cheese-chive mixture over potato slices.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes more until potatoes are tender and top is golden brown.
Garnish with fresh chives.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot gourmet deer chili
directions: Cube meat and
grind
with
hamburger plate of electric grinder.
In a large
pot, heat olive oil and saute garlic for 1 minute.
Add onion
and
ground
meat.
Cook
until
meat is done. Add next 17
ingredients;
bring
to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour,
stirring occasionally.
Slowly stir in cracker meal.
Let simmer 10 more minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve hot with crackers, Fritos or French-style garlic bread.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease
two
x 11-inch or 9 x 9-inch pans.
Pour
the batter into the baking pans and spread evenly with a rubber scraper or spoon.
Bake in the oven until the bread tests
done;
a
wooden
toothpick
or
metal skewer inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove bread from the oven.
Let the pans
cool
somewhat
on
metal
racks
before cutting into serving pieces.

title: grandma mary ann's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortenings and sugars.
Mix in honey, eggs and vanilla. Stir in cinnamon, salt, flour, baking soda, oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Next, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: orange salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in a bowl.
Sprinkle dry jello over it and mix.
Drain mandarin oranges and add.
Add nuts and mix with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook pasta by package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
Combine cooled pasta \, celery and shrimp.
Cover; chill.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Whip with wire whisk until creamy.
Cover; chill. Serve salad on bed of lettuce with dressing drizzled over top or toss until blended.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix pineapple and jello in bowl and heat in microwave for 4 minutes.
In another bowl, mix buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Combine with other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix together, cottage cheese and dry jello.
Beat.
Add cool whip and mandarin oranges, pour in dish.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours, then serve.

title: cranberry-strawberry relish
directions: A day before serving, mix cranberries and strawberries. Refrigerate.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Sift flour, soda and spices together and gradually add to cake mixture.
Melt chocolate over hot water and add to cake for a lovely rich color. Makes 3 large 9-inch layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Ice.

title: dieter's fluff
directions: Mix jello with cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Any flavor jello can be used.

title: parslied potatoes
directions: Peel a strip of skin off of potatoes in the middle.
Place potatoes in cold water.
Heat large skillet over medium-high heat. Add oil.
Saut onion and garlic for approximately 5 minutes. Add broth and 3/4 cup parsley; bring to a boil.
Place potatoes (one layer) in skillet.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove potatoes with slotted spoon to a serving bowl.
Add pepper to skillet mixture; stir.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Put into casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over broccoli.
Grate cheese and distribute evenly over broccoli.
Bake at 300° until cheese has melted.

title: spinach-rice casserole
directions: Cook for 40 minutes the brown rice and vegetable broth. Prepare the Cheddar cheese, parsley and fresh spinach while rice is cooking.
After rice has cooked 30 minutes, preheat oven to 350°. Mix cooked rice with the Cheddar cheese mixture adding garlic powder, black pepper and eggs.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole dish.
Top with mixture of Parmesan cheese, melted butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lettie's peanut butter candy
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cook until it forms a soft ball.
Add peanut butter.
Grease cookie sheet.
Pour.
Cut in squares.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix beef, green pepper, salt and pepper. Add rest of ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Put in pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.
This can also be cooked in a crock-pot.

title: garlic pasta
directions: Chop the garlic and saute in the olive oil.
Do not burn the garlic.
Add the pinch of red pepper flakes to the olive oil and garlic.
Pour the olive oil mixture over the cooked spaghetti. Add the cheese and parsley flakes and toss.

title: orange date bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Mix well.
Combine dates, juice, rind, 1 teaspoon soda and hot water.
Cool.
Add to sugar and butter mixture.
Combine flour, 1 teaspoon soda and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into standard sized, oiled loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp maska
directions: Heat olive oil in pan.
Add shrimp and spices.
Saute for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add wine and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with French bread.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Heat milk and melt marshmallows in double boiler.
Mix crushed graham crackers, candy, raisins and nuts together.
Add milk and marshmallow mixture; mix well.
Put in a well buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix jello and Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Add fruit of choice.
Pour into mold or leave in bowl.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with fresh fruit.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and garlic.
Drain well. Set aside.
Make sauce: heat soup, milk and Velveeta until melted. Add green chiles, dip mix and pimentos.
Add cheese and onions to meat.
Mix well.
Soften tortillas by dipping them, one at a time, in hot oil in shallow skillet. Drain. Fill with meat mixture. Roll and place in a greased 10 x 13 casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maryland she-crab soup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add celery and onions.
Saute until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling.
Add cream and crabmeat.
Season with nutmeg to taste.
Do not boil!

title: chicken divan
directions: Steam chicken in a little water.
Bone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Place broccoli in bottom of casserole sprayed with Pam.
Layer chicken, then sauce made of soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, black pepper and curry powder. Sprinkle with paprika.
Top with grated cheese.
Last, layer with stuffing mix combined with the melted margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rotini
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Add Prego, tomato juice, oregano and sweet basil; simmer 20 minutes. Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Grate cheese.
Layer in 2-quart casserole dish the meat sauce, macaroni, cheese, macaroni and meat sauce.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add remaining cheese on top and bake until melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave cabbage rolls italian style
directions: In 3-quart casserole, place cabbage and water.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes until leaves are pliable. While cabbage is cooking, mix together ground beef, egg, rice, onion and salt.
Divide meat mixture into 8 equal portions.
Place one portion on each partially cooked cabbage leaf and roll meat into leaf, securing with toothpick if necessary.
Return to 3-quart casserole, placing rolls seam side down.
Blend tomato sauce, sugar and oregano.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and microwave on High 15 to 17 minutes, rotating dish half turn and basting with sauce after 9 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese with mayonnaise until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve with Toast Squares.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine all together.
Shape into fairly large balls.
Place in shallow dish and bake after pouring sauce over them at 325° for 2 hours.

title: 24-hour cucumber pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in thin slices and soak in lime water for 12 to 14 hours.
Wash and soak in salt water for four hours.
Bring to a boil in strong alum water.
Pour off alum water and dip in hot boiling water.
Combine spices (in a bag), sugar, vinegar and cucumbers and simmer for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes 10 to 11 pints.

title: easy holiday salad
directions: Make jello as usual, using 2 cups boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add frozen raspberries; stir until mixed.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Pour half of mixture into dish.
Chill until firm.
Mix softened cream cheese with small amount of sour cream. Spread over jello mixture.
Top with rest of jello mixture. Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cook turkey until tender, debone as soon as cool enough.
Put in refrigerator to get cold.
Chop all ingredients in food processor individually, removing to mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to be served.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato juice.
Add spices to taste.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frogmore stew
directions: In large stockpot, add seasonings to water.
Bring to a boil. Add sausage and boil, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Add corn; count 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; count 3 minutes.
(Don't wait for liquid to return to a boil before timing corn and shrimp.)
Drain immediately and serve.
Serve with cocktail sauce, sweet and sour mustard or hot mustard.
Serves 8.

title: easy fall ratatouille recipe
directions: Saute vegetables in sun-dried tomato dressing in large ovenproof skillet until tender.
Add diced tomatoes, cook about 15 minutes, allowing some of the liquid to evaporate.
Top with cheeses and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook your squash for 12 minutes; drain. Mix sour cream, soup, onions, pimentos and water chestnuts; set aside. When squash is done, mix with sour cream mixture. Mix your dressing with 1 block butter/margarine, melted. Put one layer dressing on bottom of casserole dish; add squash mixture. Add remaining dressing to the top. Bake or put in microwave for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: irish potato cakes
directions: Mix all together and form into little cakes.
Fry in butter until brown.
Serve hot with syrup or butter.

title: granny's lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Boil last 2 ingredients, add to egg mixture and mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: pushcart palpetta(spaghetti sauce)
directions: Remove and chop the stems from mushrooms.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large skillet; saute mushroom caps, round side down first, for 3 minutes.
Turn and repeat.
Brown sausages; discard fat. Heat 3 tablespoons oil; saute mushroom stems, green pepper, onion and celery until brown.
Move to side; cook hamburg.
Cut sausages into 1/2-inch slices; return to skillet.
Add salt, oregano, basil, parsley, tomato sauce and dry red wine.
Cover; simmer slowly for 45 minutes.

title: super seafood supper
directions: Cook
celery,
green pepper and onion
in
butter
until partially cooked.
Combine these with seafood and pimento.	Mix sour cream, light cream, lemon juice and
seasonings
in
small bowl.
Combine 3/4 cup cream mixture, rice	and
drained mushrooms.	 Spread rice mixture evenly in well greased 15	x
9 x 2-inch
baking
dish.
Place seafood mixture on	top
of
rice mixture.
Pour remaining 1/4 cup of cream mixture over seafood. Combine
bread
crumbs
with remaining
butter.
Sprinkle
over casserole and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
May be prepared a day
ahead	and
refrigerated.
Allow
30	minutes
additional cooking time if refrigerated.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat prunes, cake mix, cinnamon and nutmeg real hard.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
While cake is hot, poke holes in cake layer. Mix buttermilk, sugar and melted margarine together; pour over the cake.
Heat and stir until all sugar is melted.
Bake in pan that the cake can stay in until all is eaten.

title: missy potatoes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: white christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate over medium/low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from the heat; stir in candy.
Spread on parchment paper-lined cookie sheets.	Refrigerate for 8 to 10 minutes. Break into small pieces; store in airtight containers.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until fine.
Heat milk, lukewarm only.
Dissolve yeast in milk.
Mix with dry ingredients and knead well. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in rounds or squares.
(I prefer squares.)
Brush with butter and top with another round or square and butter top.
Let rise a few minutes before baking at 350°.

title: pilaf rice
directions: Saute onion in butter in large skillet until tender, but not brown, about 5 minutes.
Add rice and saute for 3 minutes.
Add bouillon
and salt.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds and parsley; fluff with a fork.

title: bourbon bread pudding
directions: Cube bread; soak in milk.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, chopped apple, raisins and margarine.
Mix all together with hands.
Put in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until firm.

title: cheddar baked potatoes
directions: In smal bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
In a greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows. Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 10 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Cream the sugar with the oil. Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended.
Add flour sifted with the baking powder. Pour 1/2 into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

Spread the cherry pie filling over the dough. Sprinkle lightly with sugar and cinnamon. Add remaining dough and sprinkle with more cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Drizzle with powdered sugar glaze when still slightly warm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix soup and chicken broth and heat. Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Top with 1/3 of the cheese.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Can freeze.

title: oatmeal, coconut and chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Add the flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
In 1 cup of the flour, mix the baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to dough. After mixing all the dry ingredients, add and mix the chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Then add the oats.
(The mixture may be so thick that you will have to mix by hand.)
Bake at 400° on top shelf of oven.
Bake until they are light, light brown.
Take out and let cool 5 minutes on pan, then remove to rack to cool. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll to size of walnut or smaller.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: super hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes, grated Cheddar cheese and chopped onion together.
Mix sour cream, soup and melted margarine together.
Combine potato mixture and soup mixture in large bowl. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Everyone loves it.

title: n.y.  cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, beating well after each. Pour in well-greased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Shut off oven.
Leave in oven for 2 hours.
(Total:
3 hours; do not open oven door from start to end!!)

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a salad bowl.
Pour dressing over and coat well to mix.
Serve at once.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix together, then add carrots and nuts. Blend with mixer.
Pour in pan and bake (flour pans) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Don't look until 30 minutes are up.
Cool and frost; add nuts on top.

title: eggless milkless butterless cake
directions: Mix together and let come to a boil the first four ingredients.
When cool add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour into layer pans.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 350 degrees until done.
Put layers together with Powdered Sugar Icing.
Can also be baked in a loaf pan.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken; drain on paper towel.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip in egg mixture.
Add spices to flour; coat chicken.
Fry slowly in hot oil until browned on both sides (about 35 minutes), turning as needed.

title: border beans
directions: In a tall, narrow ware pot (Mexicans call it a jarrow), the beans nestle closely together and pack while cooking and it means the heat seeps gently through the jarrow as it should in cooking beans.
In order that the beans pack right, you should use enough to almost fill the pot when they swell, never less than 2 pounds. Use Mexican pinto beans.
Wash the beans; put them in the pot and fill the pot about half full of water.
Never soak pinto beans.
It causes them to be mushy.
Using a medium flame, bring the water to a boil while stirring the beans to keep them from burning.
When the water boils, turn the fire low so it can barely simmer.
It is best if you see a bubbly oozing out now and then.
Throughout the cooking, keep the water level barely covering the beans.
It makes them pack.
Be sure any water you add is boiling.
After an hour of cooking, add several chunks of salt pork.
Some people put a lid on the beans, but I do not.
It chokes off those fine odors and sometimes it causes the juices to boil over.
At the end of the second hour, cut the garlic fine (I use 6 pods).
At the end of another hour, add the oregano and chili pequins, mashed up (I use jalapeno peppers, 2 small ones, with seeds taken out).
Cook another hour.
At the end of 4 hours of cooking, add salt, one level tablespoon per each pound of beans.
Simmer 1 more hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and flour. Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick tea mix
directions: To use, add 1 teaspoon of spiced tea mixture per cup of boiling water.
Package tea in small jars.
Use a ribbon to tie a cinnamon stick (used to stir tea) to top of jar along with instructions on how to use mix.

title: king casserole
directions: Place in baking dish layer of chicken and Doritos.
Mix in chopped onion, soup and tomatoes together.
Pour over chicken and Doritos.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Drain green beans.
Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sunflower seeds or nuts. Refrigerate until firm enough to handle.
Form into ball and roll in sunflower seeds or nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: eggplant moussaka
directions: Steam eggplants for 2 to 3 minutes.
Saute onion, green pepper, garlic and celery in vegetable oil.
Add tomatoes and cook briefly (5 to 10 minutes).
Add to mixture the cracked wheat cereal and simmer 20 minutes or so until cereal is cooked.
(Add tomatoes or tomato sauce, if liquid evaporates).

title: bloody mary
directions: Shake with cracked ice.
Strain into 6 ounce glass.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: low-fat chicken in mushroom gravy
directions: Remove all visible fat from chicken breasts.
Place in casserole which has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with condensed mushroom soup and add pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
(No additional salt is needed.
Can substitute Healthy Request condensed chicken soup if desired.)

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Cream together the 1/3 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add the 1 egg and mix.
Set aside.
Heat together the baking chocolate, butter and water until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Combine the 2 cups sugar and flour.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Mix the 2 eggs, sour cream, salt and baking soda.
Add to chocolate mixture. Pour chocolate batter into a greased and floured oblong cake pan. Spoon cream cheese mixture across top and cut in with a knife to create a marbling effect.
Sprinkle top with the chocolate chips. Bake at 355° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: na-cho ordinary potatoes
directions: In square baking dish covered with plastic wrap, steam potatoes with 2 tablespoons water for 10 minutes on High in microwave, stirring halfway through.
Toss with oleo and seasonings.
Sprinkle with 1 1/4 cups cheese.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Top with chips and remaining cheese.
Cook for 2 minutes and 30 seconds on 50% power.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, milk and beaten eggs; stir until well blended.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into the pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except chicken, and put in a large oblong pan.
Put cut up chicken pieces on top of soup mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of dry onion soup mix over all of the chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: spoon bread
directions: Sift meal with salt and add boiling water.
Add butter and stir until smooth.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Sprinkle baking powder over top and stir quickly into batter.
Pour into greased pan or pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour for large pan or 45 to 50 minutes for 2 pie pan or 1/2 recipe.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Add sliced mushrooms and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Rice-A-Roni pilaf rice.

title: wanda's seven layer salad
directions: Layer the above ingredients in the order given or toss the ingredients all together.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin with 1 cup hot water.
Add strawberries, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate and let thicken.
When set, cover with a layer of sour cream.
Spread remaining gelatin mixture over the sour cream.
Refrigerate.
Unmold before serving. Serves 12.
Exchanges:
1 serving = 1 fruit, 1/2 fat.
Calories: 1 serving = 83.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Make into balls the size of meatballs.
Cook on a broiler pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 30 meatballs.

title: yeast dough for sweet buns and cherry bread
directions: Mix together yeast, milk and flour.
Let stand until spongy (20 to 30 minutes).
In a large bowl, put eggs, salt and sugar. Mix well, then add 4 cups flour.

You'll have a very soft dough. Next, add your first mixture. Beat with a spoon. Add 1/2 cup melted butter. Work butter into the dough mixture until smooth. Knead on floured surface, adding 1 more cup flour until smooth and elastic. Dough is kneaded enough when it becomes shiny and has little air pockets or bubbles in the surface.
Put dough in greased bowl and turn, leaving greased side up. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size (approximately 1 1/2 hours). Punch down and make cinnamon buns or Cherry Bread.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat oven to 350.
Roll dough into balls and bake on a cookie sheet or 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again when cold.

title: philly beef-a-roni(in honor of "adios")
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add mushroom soup, tomato paste, garlic, salt, pepper and sugar; cook slowly 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni until barely tender; drain.
Set oven at 350°.
Mix cream cheese with milk, sour cream and onion.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in large mixing bowl. Make a well in the center of mixture.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place butter/margarine in baking dish, and melt in oven. Mix sugar, flour & milk. Add peaches to mixture. Pour over melted butter. Bake at 350 degrees until light brown on top. Best to eat while warm.

title: trail side cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Makes large batch of cookies.

title: golden medley orange candied yams
directions: In saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add almonds, brown sugar and orange juice; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add yams; sprinkle with salt.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, spooning sauce over frequently.
Garnish with orange sections. Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: grandmothers tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients then cut in shortening.
Add eggs, milk, and vanilla.
Roll out dough and cut as desired.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; cut in butter with knife or pastry cutter.
Add buttermilk, unbeaten egg and vanilla; also nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pan (round).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1 cup banana pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding.
Chill. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Grease and flour an angel food cake pan or a bundt pan. Pour batter in pan and put in cold oven. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: wendy's chili
directions: In 1 tablespoon of oil, brown the ground round.
Put the can of onion soup through a blender and add to beef.
Add all the other ingredients.
Heat 20 minutes on medium to blend flavors. Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute onions over medium heat until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add spinach and continue to cook, stirring often, until no liquid is left.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir well and allow to cool.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs and cream together; gradually add to spinach mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add cheese and combine.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Place shells on cookie sheet and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted into pie comes out clean.
Serve hot or room temperature.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pastry shell.
Blend together egg, sugar, salt, tapioca and sour cream.
Pour over rhubarb and bake.

title: minestrone vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions and celery until soft.
Stir in broth and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Add frozen vegetables, pasta, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with 1/4 cup fruit juice.
Mix rest of juice (not to exceed 3/4 to 1 cup) and add other ingredients.
Let stand a few hours or overnight.
Keeps well in fridge up to 10 days.
Can be served on lettuce as a salad or as a dessert with a red cherry on top.
Can be stretched by adding more marshmallows.

title: coss hot cider
directions: Make in a 12-cup drip coffee maker glass pot or any 12-cup container.
Mix together apple cider, apple juice, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Serve hot.
This can be heated in a microwave or on top of the stove.
Keep hot on a drip coffee maker.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese and corn flakes. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Mix shortening, honey, egg and molasses.
In another bowl, sift soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and flour.
Mix wet and dry ingredients to form dough. Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter. Decorate with raisins, nuts, licorice and tiny candies. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: butter stickies(from connie's biscuit mix)
directions: Make the same way as biscuits, but roll the dough into an oblong shape.
Spread top with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with generous amounts of cinnamon, sugar and brown sugar.
Roll jelly roll fashion and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Put in greased pan; adding 1 tablespoon water to bottom.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes; turn out onto plate.

title: chicken salad (for two)
directions: In medium bowl, gently stir together chicken, apple, celery and raisins.
In cup, stir together dressing and brown sugar; pour over chicken mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 1 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter; add tomato sauce, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Put cooked noodles in greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese mixture.
Add meat, then sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and heat in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: angel hair pasta and tomato vinaigrette
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Combine tomatoes, garlic, basil, oil, vinegar and red pepper flakes in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until tomatoes are barely heated through and still firm, about 3 minutes.
Pour over drained pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's baked beans galore
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or cook in skillet; stir regularly for 20 minutes on low heat.
Great for barbecues!

title: granola
directions: Stir flours together.
Toast in heavy frying pan (no oil is needed) until well browned. Do not burn.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add wheat germ, coconut, sesame seed and sunflower seeds which have been toasted individually.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together in a large bowl eggs and sugar.
Add salad oil, flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, pumpkin and vanilla.
Put mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: veal with rosemary
directions: Cut the meat into cubes and lightly brown in hot oil, stirring frequently.
