Add the onions and cook until golden.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes.
Combine the flour and water and stir into the meat to thicken; stir.
Continue cooking until the meat is tender and the gravy thickened.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: no bake coconut cake
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over	cold water to soften.
Cook egg yolks, sugar and
flour
until smooth.
Add salt and gradually add milk. Cook
slowly
until coats spoon.
Stir in gelatine. Refrigerate 1 hour
until
cool.	Beat
egg
whites;
fold
in cooled custard. Tear
cake	into
small
pieces.
Use half to cover bottom of sheet
cake
pan.
Pour
half
of custard over cake pieces. Sprinkle half of coconut over that.
Put rest of cake, then rest of	custard,
then	coconut.
Put Dream Whip, that has been
made by directions.
(May substitute with Cool Whip.)

title: mamaw's yeast rolls
directions: Take sugar, salt and yeast, mix with flour; add the water. Mix until it gets like bread dough.
Keep adding flour until it is thick enough to knead.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 350° until golden brown; brush with butter.

title: cinnamon toast cake
directions: Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Blend milk, shortening and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on 11 x 17-inch baking sheet.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over cake.

title: two-layer cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in flour alternately with milk.
Add salt, lemon and vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles or peppers
directions: In large pan, cover cucumbers or peppers and onions with salt. Fill pan with water.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Bring cider vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed, powdered ginger, turmeric and sugar to a rolling boil.
Add drained cucumbers and onions.
Heat just to boiling and pack in hot, sterilized jars.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: In large frying pan, combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover; simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir several times while cabbage mixture is cooking.
Serves 6.

title: smicker cake
directions: Mix cake, put half of cake batter in pan and bake.
While cake is baking, melt caramels with milk and butter.
When cake is done, pour caramel, chocolate chips and pecans on top then pour other half of batter on top and bake until done.

title: k f c   biscuits
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes 6 biscuits.

title: carrot cake 2
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon, then add eggs, oil, carrots and nuts.
Mix all together well.
Pour into angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: quick carrot bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch pan (jelly roll pan) or two 8 or 9-inch square pans.
In a large bowl, blend oil, eggs and applesauce 1 minute on low speed.
Add cake mix; blend until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Stir in raisins. Pour into prepared pan; spread evenly. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes. Cool completely.
Frost with cream cheese frosting. Sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 36 bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as on package; drain well.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine soup, eggs, cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine in a bowl white sugar and cinnamon.
Place biscuits in bowl and shake until covered.
Place in tube or Bundt pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar; pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: velvet salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Boil Jell-O and pineapple juice for one minute.
Let cool and mix all ingredients together; refrigerate.

title: chicken potato and cheddar bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a 13x9 baking dish.
Place chicken in baking dish, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread broccoli and 1 1/2 c. cheese over chicken.
Place potatoes on top; bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. of cheese; bake 5 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: oatmeal bread for bread machine
directions: Measure ingredients carefully.
Place all ingredients in bread machine pan in the order recommended by the manufacturer.
Select basic cycle.
When cycle has been completed, remove loaf from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: hot dip delight
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Brown and add onions.
Add chopped apple and tomatoes, jalapeno peppers, raisins, olives, cinnamon and cloves.
Salt and pepper and add ketchup.
Add almonds (optional).

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage, then rinse in cold water.
Drain and put in 5-quart pot.
Add chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Cover pot and let cook on medium-high until cabbage is tender.
Stir often.

title: luscious lasagna(low-fat without meat)
directions: *Do not have to precook noodles.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use as a dressing for a salad.

title: meat loaf and gravy
directions: Add ingredients as listed, then mix well and pat into two pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave or in double boiler.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in broken nutmeats.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Shape into rolls on waxed paper; wrap.
Chill thoroughly or overnight.
Slice thin (1/4-inch or less).
Bake slices on greased cookie sheet in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Put sugar, shortening and salt in container you are making rolls in.
Add 1 cup boiling water to mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Beat egg and add to mixture. Add flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: apple-peanut butter dream
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: toffee bar dip
directions: Crush Heath bars.
Combine all ingredients together and mix.
Graham crackers and apples are great to dip.

title: salted spiced walnuts
directions: Wash chicken wings and pat dry.
In a bowl combine the crumbled crackers or bread crumbs, herbs and Parmesan cheese. Add seasonings and mix well to blend.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken wings, first in melted butter, then into crumb coating.
Arrange chicken wings in lightly oiled ovenproof baking dish.
Bake chicken wings at 375° for about 30 minutes or until lightly brown and done.
Chicken wings should be tender.

title: cheese cakes
directions: Blend together with electric beater.
Spoon on vanilla wafer about 2/3 full in a cup cake paper.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine cake mix with butter, chopped pecans and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Put a thin layer of mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into greased and hot iron skillets.
Bake at 325° to 350°.
May be frozen for later use.

title: 4 layer coconut dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan; dump in flour and coconut and spread mixture in bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: teriyaki marinade sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over meat and let stand at least 2 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Hard-boil the eggs.
Put eggs in cold water.
Keep changing the water to keep it cold.
Shell the eggs.
Put eggs in a container and place in the refrigerator next to the pickled beet liquid.
Next day, cover eggs with the liquid.
Put back in refrigerator for 3 or 4 days.
Stir or shake occasionally so eggs color evenly.
Serve cold.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter in a heavy 2-quart saucepan; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; stir in chicken broth gradually. Add cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken and pimento.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve immediately over toast or in patty shells.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add one ingredient on top of each other.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cool; cut in squares.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix above ingredients and press in cookie sheet with sides. Melt 1 stick butter with 12 ounces chocolate chips.
Spread over mixture and chill for at least 4 hours, better if overnight.

title: peanut butter swirl candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk; roll into a ball on waxed paper.
Put small amount of powdered sugar on paper to keep from sticking.
Roll out ball and spread with peanut butter.
Roll out with fingers into a long roll and wrap in waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator to harden.
Cut into small pieces.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with a spoon just until all is moistened.
This is an easy crust to make.
I roll the crust between wax paper and fold,
Put into pan. On the top crust I brush canned cream, then cut holes, sprinkle sugar on top and put little pieces of oleo on the holes.
I like to mix in a large tupperwear container and shape into balls.

title: cheesies potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Quarter 6 potatoes.
In a bag, shake potatoes, cheese and flour until potatoes are coated.
Place in pan and bake until brown.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes in 10 x 12-inch pan.

title: oyster sauce beef and chinese peas
directions: Combine beef, cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, sherry, oyster sauce and 1 tablespoon of the oil.
Marinate for 20 minutes.
In a wok or skillet, heat remaining oil and brown garlic.
Add meat and onion; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add peas and cook 1 more minute.

title: baked brie in phyllo
directions: Wrap the Brie in thawed phyllo dough, brushing each sheet with butter and keeping unused phyllo covered with a damp cloth.
Turn the cheese over after applying each sheet of phyllo for even distribution.
Brush phyllo wrapped Brie with butter.
Cover and refrigerate.
Before serving, place the phyllo wrapped cheese in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Garnish with fresh dill and fruit. Serves 20 to 30.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Bake pie shell 10 minutes and remove. Lower temperature to 325°.
In saucepan, melt chips with margarine over very low heat.
In large bowl beat chocolate mixture with remaining ingredients except nuts until smooth.
Stir in nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: honeyed french green beans
directions: Pour undrained green beans into a 1-quart casserole dish. Drizzle honey and Worcestershire sauce over beans. Place bacon strips on top. Bake at 350° until bacon is crisp, approximately 30 minutes. Serves 3 to 4.

title: fruit and nut pies(christmas pie)
directions: Combine cherries and pineapple in a saucepan.
Add sugar and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Sprinkle orange jello over mixture and stir until dissolved.
Cool mixture slightly.
Add bananas and pecans or walnuts.
Pour into the pie shells.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: grandma's cranberry sauce(yields 20 servings)
directions: First grind fresh cranberries (coarse grind).
Next slice seedless grapes in half.
Then grind one of the oranges, rind and all (fine grind).
Next juice the other orange.
Then add all the sugar to the fruit and juice mixture.
Stir.
Set aside.
Place water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add both boxes of jello and dissolve.
Next add dissolved jello to fruit mixture.
Now chop nuts and add to mixture.
Place mixture in container that can later be sealed. Put in refrigerator until jelled.
Now seal container.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.
Also makes nice jello mold.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain fat.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Serve.
Good warmed over with a little water added to moisten.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, layer noodles, meat sauce and cheeses; repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook ingredients over medium heat about 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done.
Beat 2 eggs and 3/4 cup sugar together.
Add this plus 1 teaspoon vanilla to rice mixture.
Cook together.
Add raisins and cinnamon as desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions, but cut down on cold water to 1 cup.
Mix cranberry sauce and add to Jell-O.
Add pineapple juice to Jell-O in place of water.
Mix other ingredients and chill.

title: fried rice
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onion and green pepper in oil until onion is tender.
Stir in rice, water chestnuts, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 5 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: sweet potato souffle #2
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: chop suey cookies
directions: Combine
the
oleo,
sugars,
eggs
and
vanilla; cream together.
Mix the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add the remaining ingredients; mix all together.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls
onto an ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crullers
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, mixing until well greased. Add flour and salt; mix well.
Shape dough into ball; chill 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 12 x 6-inch strips.
Fry in deep hot oil, 375° for 1 to 2 minutes or golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks; slowly stir in condensed milk.
Mixing well, stir in lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Spread Cool Whip on cooled pie.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine rice, soups, cheese, celery, onion, water chestnuts, egg and margarine.
Pour over broccoli and add 1/4 cup crumbled Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly hot.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Warm milk.
Mix dry ingredients and pour into milk, stirring constantly over low heat.
When thickened, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Chill and serve.

title: homemade hot cocoa
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well. Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 3 3/4 cups mix (15 to 16 servings).

title: creamy ham and cheese salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing before serving if desired.
Yields 4 servings (you can add tuna instead of ham).

title: rutabaga magic
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter with water to cover in saucepan.
Cook until tender; drain.
Mash with butter and serve immediately.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly combine cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Place about 1/4 cup cheese mixture in center of each flattened chicken breast.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup and then add sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix and add noodles.
Put in large casserole dish.
Top with grated sharp cheese.
Heat in moderate oven until bubbly.

title: tangy ham dip
directions: Mix sour cream, deviled ham, chopped chives, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Blend well.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve with potato or corn chips.

title: lazy housewife pickles
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Ready to eat in a few hours.
Keeps well a long time, covered, in refrigerator.

title: orange slice cookie
directions: Dice the pound of orange slices and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add brown sugar and flour and salt.
Mix well and add chopped nuts. Turn batter into a greased and floured jelly roll pan or 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 340° for 35 minutes.
Cut while still warm and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in double boiler until it melts, add peanuts and stir in noodles.
Mix until well covered.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator 15 to 30 minutes.

title: tropical fruit sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients in electric blender or food processor until smooth (make sure the
top is on the blender or food processor).
Pour into 1
gallon
ice cream freezer and freeze according to
manufacturer's
instructions.
Serve immediately when ready.
Makes 7 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: hot corn salad
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat; stir in green onion and carrot.
Cook, stirring, 1 minute; stir in corn, vinegar, sugar and zucchini.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring often, until hot.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix the sour cream and 1 1/2 packages Hidden Valley dressing. Fill sour cream container half full with Miracle Whip.
Add more, if desired.
Chop dill and add more, if needed.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Cook in medium size pot on medium heat until dough pulls away from sides of pot.
Add flavoring for smell and cake coloring for color.
Do not use Teflon.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a wide 6-quart saucepot.
Remove bacon and all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Save both bacon and extra fat.
Add ground beef, breaking it up with a spoon and cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Stir in onion, green pepper and garlic and cook for 10 minutes.
Add more bacon fat if needed. Mash plum tomatoes with a spoon.
Stir the tomatoes and tomato paste, bacon, 1 cup of wine and 4 teaspoons each of oregano and basil; add all remaining ingredients into the sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Taste after an hour of cooking and correct seasoning; herbs vary and so do personal notions of flavor.
If you make the sauce early, cool and refrigerate it until an hour or two before dinner.
Let it warm to room temperature before you reheat it.
Ten or 15 minutes before serving, blend in 1 teaspoon each of oregano and basil and 1/2 cup of wine.
Any leftover can be frozen for later use.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Place 2 to 3 teaspoons in cup.
Add hot water; stir.

title: twinky cake
directions: Bake cake.
Let cool.
Beat other ingredients for 10 minutes. Slice your cake in layers.
Spread filling on each layer and refrigerate.

title: terry's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Prepare Oodles of Noodles according to package.
Let cook until almost all liquid is cooked out of pot.
Add cream of mushroom soup to pot. Add can of chicken to pot.
Stir all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Quick and delicious.

title: bluebery crunch
directions: Cut in 1/3 cup Butter. Sprinkle over the filling and bake for 350° for 40 minutes.

title: no cook, no can cucumber pickles
directions: Fill 1 gallon glass or plastic jug with sliced cucumbers. Dissolve salt in enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let set for 3 days.
Pour off water, rinse 3 times in cold water.
Soak 24 hours with alum in water to cover.
Pour off and rinse 3 times in cold water.
Cover with white vinegar, let set for 7 days.
Drain vinegar off and throw away.
Rinse 1 time.
Heat 1 cup vinegar and 3 cups sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over cucumbers (will not cover pickles), add pickling spice and turmeric (put spice and turmeric in soft cloth tied up).
Let set for 24 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheeses and mix well with hands.
Add green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well again with hands.
Shape into ball.
Roll in mixture of paprika and pecans.
Chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soups, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuit pieces over hot chicken mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 5 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake until done, 20 minutes.
Melt caramels in 1/2 cup Carnation milk, then pour over cake.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix crumbs, confectioners sugar and coconut.
Add orange juice concentrate and mix well.
Form into about 1-inch balls.
Roll balls into confectioners sugar.
Store in covered container overnight.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half, remove seeds and bake cut-side down at 350° for 50 minutes.
In skillet, cook pork, celery and onion until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in salt, curry powder and cinnamon.
Cook 1 minute more.
Stir in applesauce and bread cubes.
Place stuffing in squash halves; bake uncovered 20 minutes more.
Makes 2 servings.

title: mama's green junk(beulah thomas)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
May garnish with cut up maraschino cherries for a festive look.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Fry chicken pieces in oil until brown.
Saute onions in same pan; add sherry (or other liquid).
Stir, scraping brown bits loose and blending into liquid to combine with chicken in pan.
Add crushed pineapple and water or stock and braise 25 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and bamboo shoots.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serves 20.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put
strawberries
in
pie
shell. Cook until clear the sugar, cornstarch, syrup, water and salt.	Cool slightly, then add
jello and
food	coloring.
Pour over berries. Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Wash cabbage and chop fine, then chop onions.
Heat ground beef and onions in skillet.
Put half of cabbage in baking dish. Cover with beef and onions.
Put remainder of cabbage on top. Pour undiluted tomato soup over mixture.
Bake 1 hour or longer, covered with foil, at 325°.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: In skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Brown; drain grease.
Add pork and beans, tomato sauce and hot sauce.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend the first 8 ingredients.
Blend in small amounts the flour and milk.
Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Heat nuts in oven at 250° for 15 minutes.
Cook sugar, water, salt and spices to soft ball stage.
Do not stir.
Add vanilla. Stir in nuts until creamy and thoroughly coated.
Pour on waxed paper.
Separate nuts as they cool.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: avocado corn quiche
directions: *Using your favorite pie crust recipe fit the dough into a 10-inch false-bottom quiche pan.
Line with foil and fill with rice.
Bake 10 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Remove foil and rice and bake 5 minutes longer or until lightly colored.

title: quiche
directions: Pour into deep dish Pet Ritz pie crust.
Bake as directed on pie crust at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm in middle. Let set for a few minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix shortening, sugar and salt in second bowl.
Add boiling water and mix well.
Add eggs; stir well.
Add flour and yeast.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into loaf pan or pan of similar shape.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in greased casserole.
Brown sausage and drain grease.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Top with shredded cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard with whip.
Pour over cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage delight sauce
directions: Cook sausage until light brown and drain fat.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients right in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Make 3 holes.
Put vinegar into one hole, vanilla into second hole and liquid shortening into third hole. Pour one cup water over everything.
Stir and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: valentine cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture with milk to form a dough.
Chill.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with heart shaped cookie cutter.
Place half of the cookies on a lightly greased baking sheet; brush each with water.
Cut smaller heart shaped centers from remaining cookies and place the heart frames on top of cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool; fill center heart space with cherry filling.

title: lemon snow freeze
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with 2 tablespoons of the sugar and melted margarine.
Press mixture on bottom and sides of lightly buttered refrigerator tray; chill.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Combine
with
Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon rind and juice gradually,
stirring
until
thick.
Stir
in 1 cup Baker's coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in rest
of sugar.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into tray. Sprinkle
top with remaining coconut.
Chill in freezer until firm, about
to 6
hours.
Garnish
with whipped cream, if desired.

title: dill salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: yum yum ice cream or ice cream delight
directions: Mix fruit in bowl and let stand until juices mix.
Take one scoop of ice cream and pour or spoon fruit mixture on top.
Add dash of Amaretto (almond flavored liquor).

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix 3 minutes; bake in two 9-inch buttered and floured cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Frost and fill with Pineapple Coconut Cream Frosting.

title: shipwreck hot dish
directions: Cook meat and onion with seasonings.
Drain.
Cook diced celery, carrots and potatoes.
Reserve liquid.
Combine all ingredients in a greased casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Slice tart apples to dip.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan or in the microwave, melt the chips and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press 1/2 the mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cream potato casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes just like cream potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in buttered baking dish and top with more butter and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick and easy no bake pineapple sour cream pie(very lo-cal and no sugar except in crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with spoon or fork (not electric mixer) until thick.
Pour into 1 Keebler ready crust (graham or cookie crust).
Top with lite Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Cream together crisco, margarine sugar and add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together the bananas, milk, and vanilla, add alternately with flour mixture.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine eggs, corn meal, corn, milk and oil in a bowl; set aside.
Cook beef until browned; drain well and set aside.
Pour 1/2 of corn meal mixture into a greased 1 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet.
Spread evenly with beef.
Top with cheese, onion and peppers.
Pour on remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream Crisco and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Stir in flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet, which has been rubbed with Crisco.
Bake in oven, 375°, for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in sifted confectioners sugar immediately after baking.
Cookies may be re-rolled in sugar after cooling, if desired.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter and margarine.
Add to the sugar, salt and cocoa and cream 4 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla two at a time.
Mix in flour (do not overmix).
Add nuts.
Spread evenly on greased cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with milk or water.
Bake 23 minutes at 350°.

title: poncho dreg's dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili to ground beef and heat.
Put beef and chili mixture into casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over mixture.
Place 6 slices of Velveeta cheese on top of sour cream.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Add pineapple; mix well.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vanilla sauce(for baked apples)
directions: Add all items, except vanilla.
Boil until thick (3 minutes). Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: poor man's chow mein
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery (I usually begin beef in a small amount of water and after awhile, pour away drippings).
To the beef, add onions and celery; continue browning.
Mix in casserole dish the soups, water, rice and soy sauce.
Add the browned beef mixture and stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Place topping of dry chow mein noodles on each serving.

title: harriet's chicken cantonese
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok and saute chicken until brown. Blend rest of ingredients and add to skillet.
Mix; cover and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place chicken in platter and coat with sauce.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and flavorings.
Mix and chill.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix in sauce pan.
Stir in gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute. Slowly stir at least 1/2 the hot mixture into 3 egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in 3 tablespoons butter, 1/4 cup lemon juice, 1 tablespoons grated lemon rind.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue. Bake at 400° (moderate hot oven) for 10 minutes.

title: brown bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk and stir into a soft dough.
With floured hands, knead dough lightly and quickly into a ball.
Shape dough into approximately a 7-inch round and place in a 9-inch pie plate. Cut a deep cross into the dough.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 25 minutes and then lower the oven temperature to 350° for an additional 25 minutes.
Test for doneness as above.
Let bread sit for one hour before serving.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Boil water; add tea, cover and let stand for 3 minutes. Strain; add sugar, salt, lemon juice and orange juice.
Serve hot or cold.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Blend just until combined.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and cut into small pieces.
Reserve 2 cups broth.
Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch pan.
In saucepan, mix broth and cream of chicken soup.
Bring to boil.
Pour over chicken.
In a bowl, mix margarine, flour, pepper and buttermilk to form batter.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add soup and ketchup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes, or until biscuits are done and lightly browned.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and form into balls.

title: creamy lo-cal dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients with hand beater until very smooth. Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Poke hole in bag of Doritos and crush the Doritos.
Pour both into a large bowl and stir.
Add diced tomatoes and lettuce.
Stir again.
Pour Catalina dressing in and stir until moistened.
May need to add more dressing after it soaks in.
Store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to drained broccoli.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Mix butter with stuffing. Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Put one layer of each ingredient, in order, in a large casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in casserole at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a 4-quart casserole, stirring well.
Microwave at High 12 to 13 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Stir in soda.
Microwave at High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon just until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by tablespoons onto greased wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: coca-cola cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
You may add Coca-Cola now or later.
Add cherries and pecans.
When at room temperature, place in refrigerator.
After jelling, cut and place on lettuce leaf.

title: hungry jack biscuit barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook 3 minutes to blend.
Stir constantly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each greased muffin cup.
Press in bottom and up sides to rim.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into each biscuit cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes, or until edges are brown.
Cool 2 minutes. Remove from pan.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except cheese and peppers.
Add grated cheese and jalapeno peppers.
Pour into two 9 x 12-inch pans or one 12 x 18-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese by hand with onion.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Add chili sauce slowly and mix a little at a time to blend into the cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mix.

title: betty roger's chicken casserole
directions: Saute stuffing in butter until golden.
Add 3/4 of buttered stuffing to bottom of greased 3 quart casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Mix together soup, sour cream and mushrooms. Pour over chicken.
Add remaining crumbs on top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion.
Combine with other ingredients.
Put part of crumbs in mixture and save rest to sprinkle on top.
Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan to bake brownies.
Mix eggs, butter and sugar.
Ad flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Melt chocolate and add to mixture.
Pour in pan and bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon soda over the dates.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water over the dates and soda.
Let stand.
Mix together salad dressing, sugar, vanilla, salt, flour and nut meats.
Beat well.
Add the date mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: 2 minute microwave fudge
directions: In a casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla. (Mixture will be stiff.)
Cut butter over top.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
Blend in nuts. Pour into waxed paper-lined loaf pan.
Chill one hour.
Cut into squares.

title: carolina gold barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan over medium heat, mixing well with whisk.
Heat thoroughly, whisking frequently to prevent burning.
This is great on pork, beef and chicken (see Carolina Gold Barbecue Recipe in the Meat & Main Dishes section).
If you're grilling the meat, don't put this on until the meat is cooked and ready to serve or it will burn.

title: spicy apple nut squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients by hand.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Then add apples and walnuts and/or raisins.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread mixture well into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
While still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: lemon whip
directions: Mix together and press in 9 x 13-inch pan the crackers, sugar and margarine.
In bowl, mix 1 small can frozen lemonade, Cool Whip, lemon juice and milk.
Beat with mixer and spread over crust.
Store and serve from freezer.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a bowl, combine pudding and whipped topping.
Then add crushed pineapple and juice.
Finally, stir in mini marshmallows. Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Arrange broccoli in a greased 11 x 7 x 4-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6.

title: crab soup
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler; blend in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add crab meat and seasonings.
Cook slowly over hot water for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley or paprika.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Garnish with bacon just before serving.

title: ham crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 rectangles.
Press seam smooth.
Place one slice of ham; spread with mustard and sprinkle with cheese.
Starting on short side, roll up; press to seal and roll in sesame seed.
Repeat with other rectangles.
Cut each roll into 5 slices (20 in all).
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Place slices cut side down.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix
in coconut.	Pat mixture lightly into ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 3-inches, building up slight edges.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large
mixing bowl, combine the flour and sugar.
In a heavy saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar in the bowl.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well using a wooden spoon or high speed of an electric mixer.
Pour into a well-buttered 17 1/2 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brownies test done in the center.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Chop onions and pepper.
Crush carrots.
Mix.
Add condensed milk, mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; mix well.
Let set 3 or 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: ambrosia cream cheese mold
directions: Soften gelatin in water; let mixture stand 5 minutes.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Pour juice into saucepan; heat to boiling.
Add gelatin mixture; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, lemon juice and cream cheese (a wire whisk helps to blend).
Chill until gelatin is partially set.
Fold in pineapple chunks, orange, pecans and coconut.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: rock road fudge
directions: In double boiler, mix and melt milk, butter and chocolate morsels.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and pecans.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours. Cut into squares.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put eggs in a boiler and beat well.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add milk.
Cook slow until it gets to a boil, then add vanilla extract, then cornstarch (mixed in a little milk just to make a paste).
Add to the pudding.
This will thicken and will be ready to finish. Cut the bananas, put in bowl and add 1 layer of wafers.
Add some pudding mix.
Continue until all is finished.

title: shrimp with vegetables
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium-high heat.
Add carrots, leeks, zucchini and mushrooms. Cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook until carrots are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes longer.
Remove vegetables to a plate and cover with foil to keep warm.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter and oil to same skillet and heat unti hot over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and season with salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, 2 to 3 minutes, until shrimp turn pink and are loosely curled.
Remove to a plate.
Add wine and cream to skillet and boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes to reduce and thicken sauce slightly.
Stir in Dijon and Pommery mustards, shrimp and vegetable mixture.
Heat through, about 2 minutes.
Garnish with snipped chives.

title: south of border dip
directions: Cook and stir on low heat the cheese, tomato soup, taco seasoning and Ro-Tel.
Add ground beef and rice.
Put over chips.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Add red pepper to sifted flour.
Work margarine and cheese together.
Work in flour and Rice Krispies.
Form into very small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Press each ball flat with the tines of a fork that has been dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool just slightly before removing from pan.

title: easy and fast no cook italian pudding squares
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cookies.
Mix pudding as directed on package, adding 1 teaspoon anise for each package.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak.
Slic across grain in 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Brown steak in oil in a skillet over medium-high heat for 4 to 6 minutes.
Add beef broth and next 4 ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce, stirring well.
Add to beef mixture.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add tomato wedges and toss gently.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels with water and butter.
Add pecans and vanilla. Drop by teaspoons onto buttered or Pam sprayed wax paper.
Chill.

title: strawberry salad dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Add
thawed strawberries, diced bananas and pineapple. Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold or glass dish.
Place in refrigerator
to gel.
Leave the remaining mixture at room temperature.
Whip cream.
Beat
cheese
and sugar together, fold in whipped
cream. Beat
cheese
and
sugar
together,
fold
in whipped
cream. When
mixture
in
refrigerator
gels, spread cream
mixture over it.
Chill. Carefully spoon on the remaining
half
of
fruit mixture.
Return to refrigerator to chill and set.

title: cherry delectibles(may be prepared ahead of time)
directions: Blend cheese and butter; work in flour until stiff dough is formed; chill overnight.
Drain cherries, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine cherries, reserved liquid and brandy; chill overnight.

title: squash casserole(ernestine's favorite recipe)
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain.
Let stand for 8 minutes. Saute bell peppers and onions.
Beat eggs separately in bowl. Save enough cheese to top casserole.
Combine all ingredients with squash, mixing well.
Pour into large casserole dish or large baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done or brown.

title: pauline's favorite appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Unroll crescent rolls and press into a 10 X 15 inch pan.
Seal perforations by rolling or pressing dough and push up the edges to form a crust.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and soup mix.
Drain spinach, squeeze out all the water and add to mix.
Drain artichokes and water chestnuts, chop and add.
Mix in feta cheese and garlic.
Spread spinach mixture evenly over crust. Grate Parmesan cheese over the top.
Bake 10 - 12 minutes or until heated through.
Remove from oven and cut into squares.

title: chitterling fritters(for bill colgan)
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough milk to give a pancake batter consistency.
Drop by large spoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until browned.
Bon Appetit, Bill.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Boiling fish is a favorite way
of preparing and serving fish in Denmark.
Usually only large fish are cooked this way, but slices of large fish, such as salmon, pike, halibut or carp are also excellent.
You should have a rack with 2 handles so the fish can be lifted out of the water without breaking it.
You can tie a cloth around it before it cooks.
Wash the fish well; sprinkle with salt and let stand a few minutes.
Lay on rack or tie it in a cloth, then drop it in cold water to which has been added salt and 2 tablespoons vinegar; bring to quick boil, then simmer slowly until done.
Test it with a toothpick for tenderness.
Serve with lemon sauce and parsley potatoes.

title: clam sauce
directions: In a 2 cup measure, put drained clams and enough water to make two cups. Cook garlic in oil until lightly browned. Discard garlic. Add butter and clam juice. Heat to near boil. Add clams and heat through. Do not boil. Add salt to taste and 2 Tbsp. chopped parsley. Serve over spaghetti or noodles.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and butter in large mixing bowl. Beat at high speed until creamy, scraping bowl occasionally. Add eggs, beating until blended. Stir in flour, cocoa powder, vanilla and salt.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

Bake for 25 minutes or until edges pull from sides of pan. Cool in pan on wire rack. Spread with Marshmallow Creme. Combine chocolate chips and peanut butter in a 2-quart pan. Cook over low heat until blended, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in cereal. Spread over prepared layer. Chill, covered, until set. Cut into 36 bars. Store in refrigerator.

title: peach passion salad
directions: Mix together water, boxes of Jell-O and box of vanilla pudding. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Add marshmallows and stir until melted. Add peaches and juice. Pour into dish and chill.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add remaining ingredients. Roll in shape of a pecan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. When cooled, roll in powdered sugar.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Cook turkey, celery, garlic powder, salt and pepper in 10-inch skillet.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with vegetables.
Pour tomato sauce over that.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese, then cover with rolled out crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In the early
the Labor Day celebration on the "green" was a
festive
affair on St. Helena Island.
Visitors joined the crowd
of local islanders for a gala celebration at the picnic ground,
known
as the "bay or "green".
Tables and concession stands, set
up	by
individuals from Lady's Island and St.
Helena
Island, featured delicacies such as red rice, Hoppin' John (or
peas
cooked with rice), fish, crab, shrimp, fried chicken and ham.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In casserole dish, combine eggs, broccoli, soup, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix melted butter and stuffing, then combine with other ingredients.
Put in ungreased pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Grated cheese can be put on top and melted.

title: homemade cheese dip
directions: At room temperature, cream onion, cheese and canned cream together.
Add more cream, if too thick.
Serve with chips.

title: almond cake
directions: Grease pans well, then	flour.	Cream butter, margarine and Crisco; add sugar, then eggs.
After
this	is well mixed, add baking powder, almond extract,
flour and then milk.
Bake at 325°.
Bake until golden
brown
(toothpick
inserted comes out clean).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook one fryer; bone 2nd cut into large pieces.
Cook one small package spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute in 1/4 cup butter; green peppers, celery and onion.
Add pimiento, soups, can milk.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 5-quart baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a small mixing bowl.
Place chops in glass baking dish.
Pour marinade over chops.
Cover and place in refrigerator for several hours.
Drain chops.
Reserve marinade.
Heat gas grill to medium setting.
Cook with cover down for 7 1/2 minutes on each side.
Baste with marinade.
Enjoy!!

title: mincemeat cake
directions: If you want to frost cake before baking, whip one white of egg stiff.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Turn over cake and bake.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Add from warm milk to make pourable.
Pour into hot milk; keep stirred.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool.

title: butternut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Stir in flour and salt. Add nuts; mix well.
Form stiff dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: peanut butter and walnut fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and 3/4 can of milk well.
Cook over medium heat to boiling.
Continue boiling until when by dropping in a small glass of cold water beads form in glass.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, peanut butter and nuts.
Stir and beat until mixture starts to thicken.
Pour onto well buttered cookie sheet.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak bread in water.
Squeeze out excess water.
Combine bread, ground beef, egg, seasonings, onion and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Mix well with a fork.
Shape into a loaf in a shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients (1/2 cup tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and water).
Pour mixture over meat loaf and bake 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Boil potatoes (sliced) and drain.
Layer beef and potatoes.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of water or milk, then pour over beef and potato layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: the 8-minute light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve jello completely in boiling water; stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until jello is thickened, about 2-3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using a wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip; then whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound up.
Spoon into prepared pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish, if desired.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with slightly moist bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet 'n' sour cabbage casserole
directions: Cook the cabbage in 1 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat, drain well and place in a 1-quart casserole.
Fry the chopped onion until crisp, remove from pan and set aside.
Blend the flour and brown sugar into the bacon drippings in the pan.
Stir in the beer and vinegar.
Add pepper, 1/4 teaspoon salt and the onion; cook lightly until onion is limp.
Return the chopped bacon to the mixture.
Pour this sweet-sour mixture over the cabbage and cook about 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macadamia nut brittle
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Equally distribute Macadamia nuts over bottom of dish.
Set aside.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes. Put in crock-pot.
Add chili when cheese is starting to melt.
Keep stirring.
Serve with chips.

title: cayenne chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large pan, sprinkle with seasonings of cayenne pepper and garlic powder.
Cover with onion slices; bake at 400° until chicken is done.
Spread picante sauce over chicken and over sauce the grated cheese.
Return to oven just until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips and salad.

title: hamburger junk
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Season with garlic salt, oregano, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese to taste. Add tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Let simmer.
Put half of the sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish, then half of the macaroni. Repeat layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and sharp cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Cut 5 or 6 peeled apples into small pieces.
Sprinkle with 5 teaspoons cinnamon (or to your taste) and set aside.
In a large bowl mix ingredients (except apples) until smooth.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture into a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan; add 1/2 apple mixture.
Add remaining cake mixture to pan and top with remaining apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cake will be golden brown when done.
Remove from pan immediately and cool.
Best served cool or cold.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients until thick, stirring often.
Pour into quart jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: jagerschnitzel(veal in brown gravy and mushrooms)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Pound cutlets with a meat tenderizer to flatten them.
Season cutlets with salt and pepper, dredge them in beaten eggs and then coat evenly with bread crumbs.
Place cutlets into skillet and fry until golden brown (1-2 minutes in each side).
Remove the meat from the skillet and drain on paper towels.
Keep the meat warm in the oven while you make the gravy.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup; add cream cheese, stirring, until thoroughly blended.
Soak gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to soup mixture.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until evenly mixed.
Pour into oiled fish or any mold.
Place in refrigerator to set.
When ready to use, turn out on platter. Serve as spread on crackers or as a salad.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling salted water.
Meanwhile, melt 1 1/2 rolls of garlic cheese and 1 stick of margarine.

title: pumpkin waffles
directions: Sift together pumpkin, eggs, milk and butter.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Bake in waffle iron.

title: moravian mints
directions: Simmer granulated sugar and water together until syrup threads from spoon.
Take from stove; add confectioners sugar, cream of tartar and peppermint.
Beat until creamy and drop from spoon onto wax paper.
For wintergreen flavor, use wintergreen extract and pink coloring, peppermint extract with green coloring and lemon extract with yellow coloring.

title: passover muffins
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add oil.
Add matzo meal.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly after adding each egg.
Place in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Makes approximately 12 large muffins.

title: summer chicken
directions: Mix all the wet* ingredients with ginger and mix well.
Cut vegetables and put them all in the marinating dish with the chicken and marinade.
Place dish in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Mix the marinade every once in a while.
Place vegetables and sauce in a tin pan or tin foil.
Place it on the top rack or on the side of grill.
Grill chicken until done.
Serve with white or wheat rice.
It's good.

title: braised cabbage, kielbasa and spuds
directions: Cut cabbage and potatoes in 1-inch chunks.
Mix broth with mustard in a large saucepan.
Add the cabbage and potatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add kielbasa; cover and cook 5 minutes or until hot.
Serve with mustard.
Serves 4.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and milk; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill at least one hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Chill other half of dough until ready to use.
Cut in desired shapes with cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Boil 4 to 6 chicken breasts.
Oil a casserole dish.
Line with Doritos (regular flavor).
Put a layer of chicken that has been taken off the bone on top of the Doritos.
Mix together cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour on top of chicken.
Place a layer of Doritos on top and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces in 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon mixture and drop into buttered Bundt pan.
In saucepan bring to boil 1/2 cup sugar, white corn syrup, 1 tablespoon cinnamon, butter and nuts.
Pour over biscuits and bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tasty potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and slice potatoes.
Combine with celery, onions, green peppers, pimentos and seasoning.
Add Dressing.
Mix well and chill.
Add additional dressing before serving.

title: pat's chicken enchiladas
directions: Place tomatoes, chili peppers, coriander and salt in blender; blend until smooth.
Add sour cream and blend.
Set aside.
Mix chicken, cream cheese and onion, also salt to taste, if desired.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook and stir onion in oil, using 10-inch skillet, until tender.
Add all ingredients except tomatoes.
Cook and cover over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes. Cover and simmer until green pepper is tender, approximately 5 minutes.

title: chili con queso nacho dip
directions: Cut Velveeta into cubes and put into crock-pot or microwave-safe bowl.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes or salsa.
Melt together.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Follow directions on back of sparerib mix.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar (let stand).
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir in apples and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add to mixture.
Mix well, adding nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken and wine(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Place chicken skin side up in baking dish 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Place in refrigerator to jell.
Mix lemon jello and 1 cup boiling water. Add marshmallows and cream cheese.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend mayonnaise, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Chill until thick, then spoon over red jello.
Mix lime jello, 2 cups boiling water and cold water or ice cubes.
When thickened, gently pour over lemon mixture and jell.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place bread as a liner in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then sausage. Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper. Pour over sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until eggs are set. Serves 6 to 8.

title: forgotten short ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs.
Put in Dutch oven.
In small pan combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over short ribs.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours or until tender.
Spoon off excess fat prior to serving.

title: dutch cookies
directions: Cream butter/margarine. Add sugar and cinnamon; beat well. Add egg yolk; beat well. Sift and add flour. Mix well. Press dough evenly unto greased cookie sheets or 12
x 15-inch pan. Brush with slightly beaten egg white. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and pecans. Bake 30-35 minutes at 300°. Cut into squares while warm.

title: black-bottom goodies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Make a well in center of mixture. Combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients, stirring well. Spoon batter into paper-lined miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Combine cream cheese and next 3 ingredients, stirring well. Stir in chocolate morsels. Spoon about 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: beet wine(5 gallons)
directions: *Used in flower and root wines because natural yeast is absent in these crops and it helps to carry fermentation further.

title: banana popsicles
directions: Whiz for 3 minutes in blender.
Put in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and chill.
Cut a banana in half.
Use a corn dog stick or fork.
Roll banana in carob mixture.
Then roll in coconut, peanuts, walnuts or anything else you desire.
Place on tray covered with wax paper and freeze.
Take out and let the kids or grown-ups have fun.
Delicious treat and low-fat.

title: no salt bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually add, by hand, rest of flour.
Makes a soft batter.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Punch down.
Beat 25 strokes.
Knead lightly.
Spread in greased pan; let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: zucchini slaw
directions: In large bowl, toss zuchini with carrot and green onions.
In a small screw-top jar, combine remaining ingredients; cover and shake well.
Pour over vegetable mixture and toss to combine. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil and cook for 1 minute.
Set off heat and add vanilla.
Beat until right consistency to spread.
Spread on cooled cake layers.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
In casserole dish, beat egg yolks with cream.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add corn and butter and mix.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into prepared pan and sprinkle top with paprika; bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.	Chill and serve.

title: onion pretzel snacks
directions: Break pretzels into bite size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and add onion soup mix.
Stir well.
Pour over pretzels and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: mock lemon pie
directions: Mix and cook together the first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and lemon extract; cook a little bit more.
Cool and pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites; add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top and brown in hot oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Add peanut butter and beat in well.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip and spoon into pie shell. Top to taste with more Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Start in cold oven.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Butter top 15 to 20 minutes before done.

title: mashed potato filling
directions: Saute in olive oil onion, celery, garlic and poultry seasoning.
Mix with bread.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Butter 8 x 8-inch pan.
Slice peaches and put in the bottom of the pan.
Cut bread into 5 finger slices and put on top of the peaches.
Mix butter, flour, sugar and egg.
Pour over bread. Sprinkle with a little cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients, mix thoroughly and store in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Do not mix second time.
Fill muffin cups and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. May add any fruit variation.
Will keep well in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Boil Jell-O, water and pineapple for 3 minutes.
Add marshmallows, pecans, cottage cheese and whipped cream.
Cool in icebox.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Break cauliflower into sections.
Cook for 10 minutes in boiling water, which has been salted.
Drain well.
Combine cauliflower with 2 tablespoons margarine, onion, cheese, sour cream and salt.
Spoon into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Melt remaining margarine and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over the cauliflower mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: oven-buttered corn chunks
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Add milk and corn.
Stir until soft dough is formed.
Turn out on a well floured board or pastry cloth. Knead about 15 times.
Roll out in a rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1-inch strips and then into 24 pieces.
Roll in the melted butter and arrange in the pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crush taco
chips
into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown ground beef; season
with envelope taco seasoning.
Add refried beans to beef; mix
well.
Then add layer of meat and chips, then 1 layer thick of
shredded
cheees.
Add
1 layer of sour cream. Bake 15 minutes at
Leave set 5 minutes before eating. Add 1/2
head of chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes and chopped black
olives.
Add more
Cheddar
cheese
sprinkled
on top; serve.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add onion and celery; saute about 10 minutes.
Add peppers and shrimp; saute 15 minutes more until shrimp are done.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and sauce mixes; stir well to get out the lumps.
Add 1 quart of milk.
Return to low heat and bring to a simmer slowly, until it thickens.
Add more milk; thin out if necessary.
Add parsley at the end of cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Place in casserole dish and cover with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Melt butter and combine with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and crackers are browned.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla, water and nuts or coconut.
Turn into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or less in a 350° oven.

title: county kitchen chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth; cut chicken into small pieces and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a saucepan, mix and bring to a boil the reserved broth and soup.
In another bowl, combine margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly to form batter.
Pour broth mixture over chicken.
Spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 3 layer cake pans at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry bacon. Remove from fat. Add onions and green pepper. Fry until slightly browned. Pour in soy sauce. Stir. Combine rice and meat. Add to onion mixture. Salt and pepper to taste. Heat. Add unbeaten egg and stir until blended well with rice. Crumble bacon over top.

title: cordon bleau
directions: Pound chicken.
Season with salt.
Place ham and cheese on each.
Tuck in sides and roll, pressing to seal.
Coat with flour. Lightly brown in butter; place in a baking dish.
Stir mushrooms, water, wine and Heinz 57 sauce in butter in skillet.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender. Thicken sauce and serve with rice.

title: nanaimo bars
directions: Combine crumbs, coconut and nuts; reserve.
Heat butter and 1/4 cup granulated sugar until butter is melted.
Stir in cocoa; mixture should be smooth and sugar dissolved.
Blend in egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine mixture with crumb mixture.
Turn into a lightly oiled (not greased) 8 x 8-inch pan.
Press firmly to make a smooth surface.
Place into freezer while preparing next layer.
Blend the 1/4 cup soft butter, the powdered sugar and hot water until mixture is smooth and well combined.
Spread over chocolate layer, smoothing top.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over top of cookie (sometimes it spreads easier if you add a little butter and milk.)
Cover and chill.
Cut into 16 bars (288 calories each!).

title: squash casserole
directions: Put squash in large casserole dish & mash.
Add cheese leaving enough to cover later.
Stir in crackers & minced onions. Add eggs & stir quickly to prevent them from cooking.
Salt & pepper to taste.
Cover with rest of cheddar cheese.
Cook at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 20 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: tuna-zucchini frittata
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in 8 or 9-inch skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
In large bowl, beat eggs with milk.
Add mushrooms zucchini, tuna, salt, lemon juice and tarragon.
Mix well.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Pour in tuna mixture.
Cook over low heat to medium heat, without stirring, until frittata is set on bottom.
Place under broiler and cook just until top is set, about 3 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sunflower dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies, place half crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into marble-size balls. Bake in 400° oven until brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine water, honey and oil in saucepan and heat to lukewarm. Pour into a large mixing bowl and re-check temperature.
Stir in the powdered milk, salt, yeast and 3 cups
whole wheat flour.

Mix well. Add the rest of the whole wheat flour and enough unbleached flour to make a nice springy dough. Turn out onto a floured board and knead until smooth, about 10 to 15 minutes. Put dough into an oiled bowl, turning to coat all sides. Cover and let rise until double, about 60 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Line baked, cooled pie shell with 2 cups of large, uncooked berries, arrange hulled side down.
Make a sauce of the other 2 cups of berries, cut up and cooked until thick with sweetening, water, cornstarch and salt, mixed together.
Remove from heat. Add butter and stir well.
Cool and pour over berries in the pastry shell.
Spread with a thick coating of whipped cream or whipped topping.
Serves 6.

title: mushrooms with crabmeat stuffing
directions: Saute stems, onions and celery in butter until celery is tender.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add breadcrumbs, parsley, white crabmeat, garlic, salt & pepper.
Mix well and add more melted butter if too dry.
Lightly blanch mushroom caps.
Drain and cool. Form small balls of stuffing and insert into each cap.
(In forming balls, stuffing should not stick to your hands.)
Lightly sprinkle with garlic.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
(Excess stuffing may be frozen or formed into crab patties and baked.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken and sour cream; set aside.
Pour melted butter over potatoes; pour cream of chicken mixture over potatoes and mix well. Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and bake in unbaked crust in 375° oven for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time.
Add rum and vanilla.
Add alternately flour, baking powder and milk, then add nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven about 80 minutes.

title: beach cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl, then pat it out into a 9 x 12 inch pan, sprayed with Pam. Mix the next 3 ingredients and pour over crust. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 45 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: honey salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in a jar and shake.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Put ingredients in punch bowl and let stand for 15 minutes. Then pour 2-quarts ginger ale over sherbet and strawberries.

title: rosemary chicken and mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Spread lightly with mayonnaise and sprinkle with salt and lemon pepper.
Arrange chicken cubes in shallow layer in nonstick skillet and brown quickly over high heat, turning once.
Remove and set aside. Combine onions, wine, rosemary and mushrooms in skillet.
Cook and stir over high heat until most of liquid evaporates and onions and mushrooms begin to brown.
Return chicken to skillet and heat through.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve over pasta.

title: sue siegel's stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into ovenproof casserole and cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Do not remove cover until ready to serve.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and stir in the seasoning. In large round casserole, layer meat, then cheese, then tortilla. Repeat until all is used. Put beans and sauce on top. Cover with more cheese. Bake in oven until bubbly and hot, for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with sauce and sour cream.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a full boil.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Add ice water and celery.
Put into refrigerator until jello starts to mold.
Whip evaporated milk and fold into jello mixture.
Chill.

title: hot cherry pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
To Bisquick add sugar and the drained cherries.
Stir in milk to make a stiff dough.
Spread in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan or 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Heat the juice from the cherries with water added to make 1 1/4 cups and the remaining cup of sugar.
Also add 1/2 teaspoon almond extract and a few drops of red food coloring.
Add butter and bring to a boil.
Pour over the dough and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: hungarian  paprikas
directions: Saut onions in 2 Tbsp. shortening, drain.
Add to the onions the red pepper and paprika, salt and water.
Add cut up chicken and cook until tender about 2 hours.

title: garden vegetable onion dip
directions: Stir together sour cream, onion soup mix, garlic powder, and dill weed until well blended. Stir in grated carrots. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Bake small red potatoes.
Fry bacon crisp, drain.
Chop potatoes, bacon, eggs and onions.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
May be served warm or cold.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Drain excess fat.
Mix all ingredients together with meat.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Can be cooked in crock-pot on high.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.

title: mint salad
directions: Melt jelly over low heat.
Add salad dressing.
Blend well. Stir in marshmallows, pears and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: leek, potato and sausage soup
directions: In a dry, heavy saucepan, toast the cumin and caraway seeds over moderate heat, stirring for 2 or 3 minutes.
Transfer to a plate.
In the pan, cook the leeks in the butter, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Stir in the broth and the potatoes (cut into 1/2 inch cubes).
Bring the liquid to a boil.
Simmer the mixture for 10 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.
Stir in the toasted seeds, Kielbasa, cream, and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer the soup for 5 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in the spinach.
Serves 4.

title: corn fritters
directions: Measure water into large mixing bowl.
Add yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, shortening, salt and egg.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place for 40 minutes.
Stir down.
Stir in corn.

title: canjica(corn pudding)
directions: Cook the corn as you would dried beans or peas until tender (20 minutes in the pressure cooker is one way).
Don't use a lot of water.
After the corn is done, add other ingredients.
(You may need more milk, coconut and sugar, depending on how the corn comes out.)
Before serving, sprinkle with cinnamon.
The texture should be creamy, but lumpy and not too thick.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate cheese pie(in microwave)
directions: Prepare and microwave crust as directed; set aside.
Place cream cheese in medium mixing bowl; microwave at power level 5 for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cream cheese softens.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended; set aside.
Place chocolate in small bowl.
Microwave at power level 5 for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until chocolate can be stirred, stirring 1 or 2 times.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add sour cream; beat at low speed until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust.
Place on saucer in oven.
Microwave at power level 5 for 12 to 15 minutes or until center is slightly set, rotating pie plate every 3 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Chill for 6 hours or until set.
Top
with cherry pie filling.

title: sausage roll
directions: Make dough with flour and margarine.
Roll into a rectangle. Spread raw sausage over dough.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Chill, slice and bake at 400° until sausage is done and dough is brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple evenly over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (which has been greased).
Cover with pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
