Dot margarine evenly on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: good cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oats and chips. Stir in oats and chips. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: baked ham slice-sauterne
directions: Place ham in a shallow baking pan.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in water and margarine.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in large skillet and saute chopped onion over medium heat.
Add meat and saute 5 minutes or until browned.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream in order listed.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and cook just until heated through.
Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or egg noodles.

title: oranged barbecued wings
directions: Split chicken wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry. Season wings with salt and pepper.
Place wings on broiler pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Combine barbecue sauce, orange juice, Worcestershire sauce, rind, cloves and garlic in saucepan. Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Brush sauce over wings.
Yields 8 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cream together all ingredients. Chill in refrigerator overnight. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in a buttered 13 x 9-inch Pyrex.
Add soup and water; mix well.
Place chicken on rice.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: mixed-up hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soups, water, onions and cheese.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easy italian cream cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat together cheese, soups, Ro-Tel and onions.
After cheese melts, add broken chips and chicken.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white punch
directions: Mix all together in large punch bowl.
Serves about 75 people.

title: red and white strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix jello with water.
Add partially thawed strawberries, stir well.
Add bananas and pineapple.
Place 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator until firm. Put sour cream on top.
Put the rest of the strawberries mixture and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into square to serve.
Dessert of salad.

title: sherry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix and nutmeg in large bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix at low speed until moistened, then beat at medium speed 3 minutes, or beat by hand 150 strokes per minute!
Turn batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake, below oven center, in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake tests done.
Remove from oven and let stand in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack and glass, if desired.

title: cheese logs
directions: Grate and mix all cheese together.
Add chili powder and garlic salt to taste.
Roll in crushed nuts.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients until it spins a thread. Then add soda and pour over one gallon popped corn.

title: low-fat key lime pie
directions: Mix frozen limeade, milk and Cool Whip. Beat with mixer. Pour into pie shell and chill 2 to 4 hours before serving.
Garnish with cut-up lime slices and stemmed cherries.
Keep any leftovers in refrigerator.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Ready to serve when strawberries are thawed.
Looks great when served in clear or crystal bowl.

title: garlic cheese dip
directions: Combine
sour
cream,
salad
dressing	mix and parsley flakes in a small bowl;
chill several hours to blend flavors. Serve with crackers or crisp vegetable sticks.

title: fruit wake-up
directions: Combine banana, pineapple and orange juice in bowl.
Chill in refrigerator.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Top with toasted coconut.

title: cappuccino shake
directions: In a blender, combine milk, coffee crystals, sugar and extract.
Blend until coffee is dissolved.
Serve with a dash of cinnamon.
For a hot drink, pour into a mug and heat in a microwave.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well, add sugar. Blend in oil and vanilla. Add zucchini. Add dry ingredients, then pineapple, raisins, nut, and coconut. Mix well. Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans (don't fill too full). Bake 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Place wings in single layer on baking pan.
Combine all ingredients in a sauce pan and bring to a simmer.
Pour over wings and bake at 350° 1 hour.
Pan may be covered for first 20 minutes of baking.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Chop cherries, pineapple, dates and pecans in a large pan. Add soda and salt to flour; add to fruit.
Mix until fruit is well coated.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Hat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix together thoroughly sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk, mashed bananas and flour, then soda and fold in chopped nuts.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar. Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: wendy's cheesy potatoes
directions: Fully cook potatoes in skin in microwave.
After cool, peel skins off and cut in pinwheels.
In casserole dish, make a layer of potatoes.
Put cheese strips on top of potatoes.
Continue to make layers until you have used up the potatoes.
Empty cream of chicken soup into separate bowl.
Mix well with one soup can of milk, then pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese strips.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in oven uncovered at 400° for approximately 30 minutes or until cheese is completely melted throughout the casserole dish.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, brown beef and drain.
Add onion, salt and pepper, then stir.
Add sliced potatoes, soup and water.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: special mashed potatoes
directions: Make mashed potatoes.
Add cream cheese, eggs, flour and minced onion.
Put in baking dish.
Top with French fried onion rings. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pasta with artichokes
directions: Trim artichokes and prepare as for hearts, cutting in halves or quarters.
Or, if using frozen artichokes, thaw and use as they come in the package.
Saute onion in butter until translucent.
Add garlic, wine, lemon juice and artichokes.
Cover and cook over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Add heavy cream and cook, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes longer until mixture thickens slightly.
Add fresh fettuccine, cooked, chopped nuts and Parmesan cheese.
Toss, then add salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
Serve with warm soup, sourdough French bread and Chardonnay wine for a Monterey Bay, California experience.

title: fourth of july dip
directions: Spread beans in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Top with sour cream and then pour melted cheese over sour cream.
Top with sliced jalapenos.
Serve with chips.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark in 200° oven.
Stir in peanut butter; add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Cool until hardened.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix
first
five
ingredients
together.
After this is well blended, add flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour in 2 greased and floured
loaf
pans
or 1 (13 x 9-inch) cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat peanut butter and syrup over medium heat until warm and soft, stirring constantly.
Mix in cereal until well coated.
Press into greased pan and refrigerate until hard.
Cut into 18 bars.

title: hearty chicken pot pie
directions: Combine broth, 1 c. water, carrots, and potatoes in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer over low heat 10 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Divide the okra evenly between 3 (1 pint) jars.
Place one dried chile and one tsp. of dill into each jar.
In a small saucepan, combine the water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over the ingredients in the jars, and seal in a hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Refrigerate jars after opening.

title: chicory(cooked greens)
directions: Clean and wash one head of chicory.
Cut into manageable eating size.
In a proper size pot, place 2 cups water, pinch of sugar, pepper, tomato sauce (for taste and color) and the press of 2 large cloves garlic.
Add the cut greens to the pot containing the listed ingredients and cook, covered, at medium heat, until done (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Enjoy with toasted French or Italian bread.

title: sauerkraut and noodle dough
directions: Place sauerkraut and water in 4-quart size saucepan.
Begin heating.

title: basic crepes
directions: In mixer bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Add melted margarine or butter and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth. (Batter will be thin.)
Pour scant 1/4 cup butter into lightly greased and heated 8-inch crepe pan or skillet.
Tilt pan to coat bottom evenly with batter.
Cook over medium heat until brown; turn crepe to brown second side.
Cool pan slightly between crepes.
Spoon filling onto center of crepe and roll.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put all ingredients except milk in pan; bring to boil, stirring constantly, then add milk and bring to boil again.
Boil until it forms a soft ball.
Mix with popcorn and form balls.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 325°
oven, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli-cheese potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; add chopped onions.
Cover with water. Cook together for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, cheese, broccoli, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve with Broccoli Cornbread.

title: pineapple almond slaw
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a small bowl; set aside. Combine cabbage and remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add sour cream mixture.
Toss well, cover and chill.

title: parmesan cheese potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place butter into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and melt in oven.
Mix Parmesan cheese, flour, salt and pepper in a bowl with a cover.
Place potatoes into the mixture.
Shake until well coated.
Place in pan and sprinkle leftover mixture over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb pudding cake
directions: Combine together 1 cup sugar, flour, butter, baking powder and milk; pour into 9-inch square pan.
Over this batter put rhubarb, 1 cup sugar and boiling water.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer. Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients. Gradually add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in raisins. Drop dough by 2 teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies (60 calories per cookie), 1.5 g fat, 00 mg cholesterol.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in olive oil.
In casserole dish, combine the rest of ingredients.
Add the onions and pepper. Cover and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until rice is done. Stir to mix the rice and vegetables.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Spoon into buttered casserole dish, sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 layer pans and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Let layers completely cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar and press into large oblong cake pan. Bake 8 minutes at 400°. Cool completely. Beat cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar until smooth; add Cool Whip and mix. Spread over pretzels. Seal edges and refrigerate until firm. Mix jello, 2 cups boiling water and berries. Let set up slightly, then pour over cream cheese mix and refrigerate. Keeps fine so you can make day ahead.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add most any kind of fruit except for blueberries.
Combine and chill.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in Tupperware bowl the lettuce, cauliflower and peas. Sprinkle Italian seasoning mix on top.
Cover with mayonnaise and seal around edges.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon crumbs on top. Cover and refrigerate.

title: yogurt cheese
directions: Line large sieve with double thickness of cheesecloth.
Add yogurt.
Set over bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Use with baked or mashed potatoes, as a spread or in dips.

title: croque monsieur
directions: Cut a slit in each bread slice to form a pocket.
Spread 1 tsp honey mustard into each bread pocket.
Divide ham and cheese evenly among bread pockets.
Combine milk and egg whites in a shallow bowl, stirring with a whisk.
Dip sandwiches, 1 at a time, in milk mixture, turning to coat.
Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium high heat.
Add 2 sandwiches; cook 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Repeat procedure with remaining sandwiches.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pineapple-coconut dessert
directions: Beat together egg yolks, sugar and salt. Add to milk that has been scalded and cooled. Cook over hot water in double boiler until custard coats spoon.

title: sunday morning brunch
directions: Mix eggs, salt, 1 cup of milk, mustard and soup with remaining 2/3 cup milk.
Layer bread, sausage, cheese, mushrooms and egg mixture in a rectangular cake pan.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cut slice from top of bread loaf; remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite size pieces.
Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add process cheese spread; stir over low heat until process cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Spoon into bread loaf.
Serve with vegetable dippers and bread.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli (do not add salt).
Saute onions in margarine.
Add soup, mushrooms, cheese and broccoli.
Heat well and serve with large corn chips.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and powdered sugar (will turn liquid) until it makes a ball like dough.
Divide and roll out on powdered sugar. Spread peanut butter over and roll up jelly roll style.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Slice and eat.

title: yulonda's homemade sweet spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Brown hamburger and drain grease from meat.
Stir in barbecue sauce and add water and sugar.
Stir all together.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a 9 x 13-inch rectangular cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Grease and flour pan.

title: chicken scala
directions: Flour chicken breasts and brown in oil. Drain fat from pan and add consomme to chicken; simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup sour cream to make a creamy sauce. Add several shakes of black pepper.
Put chicken and sauce in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and brown under broiler.

title: mock lobster
directions: Thaw- have a large pan of water boiling with about 1 cup sugar (1/2 cup sugar/lb. fish).

title: green tomato pickles
directions: You will also need 3 clean quart jars.

title: fried pies
directions: Roll out biscuits real thin and put fruit in side.
Cut around edges.
Fry in oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: raspberry brownies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cream margarine, eggs and sugar, then add chocolate.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Drop jam by teaspoonfuls over surface of batter. Swirl with fork to mix into batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown on top.

title: ginger cup
directions: Push the cloves into the oranges and let them stand an hour that the flavor may be extracted.
Rub the sugar over the rind of the oranges and lemons, then add juice of these to the sugar.
Add the spices and pineapple and let stand two hours.
At the time of serving, put in the water and ginger ale and pour over the cracked ice.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix and follow advice in Proverbs 23:14 for making a good boy. Put all in one pan.
Bake for 3 hours in moderate oven.

title: alabama apples(roll tide!)
directions: Put butter in bottom of casserole; add sliced apples and sugar.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in measuring cup with warm water.
Stir together flour and salt in large mixing bowl.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in dissolved yeast.
Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead just until smooth.
Place dough in large greased bowl; turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm draft-free area until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Divide dough in half.
On floured surface, roll each half into an 11-inch circle.
Place rounds on greased 12-inch pizza pans.
Make pizza as desired. Bake at 400°. Makes 2 pizzas.

title: consomme rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese-macaroni salad
directions: Chill macaroni.
Combine with celery, peas, carrots and green pepper.
Season to taste.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Mix lightly with two forks.
Serve on any crisp salad greens.
Garnish with cheese balls or diced stuffed olives.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: beef goulash(microwave)
directions: Place beef in a 3-quart microwave casserole.
Peel tomatoes and remove cores.
Cut tomatoes in chunks.
Place in casserole with beef.
Add onion, salt and pepper; stir.
Cover and cook on Roast for 40 to 50 minutes or until beef is tender.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Stir sour cream into mixture and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with blueberry pie filling.
(May also be topped with cherry pie filling.)

title: sausage bake
directions: Braise sausage and drain grease off.
Add flour to sausage and add all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream the oleo, Crisco and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs. Sift together the flour and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Form into a ball.
Roll out on floured board to the thickness you desire and cut out.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen, according to thickness.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, beat in sugar and other ingredients.
Add enough flour (about 1/2 cup) to make mixture stiff enough for drop cookies (on a greased sheet) with floured fork, crisscross.
Bake at 350°. Makes 60.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in pan.
Cook 5 or 6 minutes.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Pour in buttered cake pan or plate.
Let cool!

title: company french toast
directions: Pour melted butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan and cover with brown sugar. Place a layer of bread (as close as possible) over butter; sprinkle cinnamon and raisins over and cover with another layer of bread. Combine and beat eggs, vanilla and milk; pour mixture over bread. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: wild rose jelly
directions: Measure rose petals.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Boil 15 minutes.
Strain through a jelly bag.
Add strawberry juice and measure the liquid.
If you do not have a quart, add enough water to make up the difference.
Return to kettle.
Stir in sugar and bring to a boil.
Still, stirring, pour in pectin and boil 1 minute more.
Pour into jelly glasses and seal with paraffin.

title: french eggs
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay bread in 2 layers in pan. Cover each layer with grated cheese; sprinkle with bacon.
Mix eggs, milk and salt together; pour over top.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: williamsburg chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate baskets
directions: Crush shredded wheat biscuits until fine.
Melt chocolate in double boiler until soft.
Stir in peanut butter and add mixture to shredded wheat.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Shape into birds nest and place jelly beans in each one.
Chill.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add self-rising flour; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine pecans, walnuts and all-purpose flour in bowl; toss to coat.
Fold into batter.
Stir in apples.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: green beans and new potatoes
directions: Place beans, pork, onion, salt, sugar and water in Dutch oven. Cover and cook 1 hour. Add potatoes and cook 30 minutes longer or until tender.

title: pineapple cream cheese gelatin mold
directions: Cook sugar and pineapple 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add gelatin to sugar and pineapple and chill.
Beat in separate bowls the cream cheese and Dream Whip. When pineapple is cold, beat in the cream cheese and the Dream Whip until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Place in mold and refrigerate.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put in baking dish, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour batter into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: green beans and ground beef
directions: Brown onion and garlic lightly in fat. Add beef and cook stirring with fork 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce and 3 cups of water. Heat to boiling.
Add beans and cook 10 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch blended with a little water.
Cook slowly 10 minutes longer, stirring often.
Serve on
hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
except cracker crumbs. Put into buttered casserole and top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Tasty!

title: molly's pork chops
directions: Mix soup and water and set aside.
Place pork chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Slice onion and green pepper on top of each chop. Pour tomato soup over the top.
Cover with tinfoil, vent foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: thyme-lime chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt butter in olive oil; add lime juice, thyme, lime peel, garlic, salt and pepper.
Place chicken on a greased broiler pan. Brush with sauce.
Broil, basting frequently, 6 to 7-inches from the heat, for 15 to 20 minutes on each side or until the chicken juices run clear. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Fix jello accordingly, add remaining ingredients and chill in freezer over night. Enjoy!

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, oil and enough water to mix dough well.
Let set and rise about 2 hours or longer.
Roll out thin; cut in strips. Break into small pieces, about 2-inches or shorter.
Cook chicken; add bouillon to taste.
Add salt if needed.
Cook dumplings in broth; add chicken after they are cooked.
Add a little yellow food coloring for color.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in next 2 ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cool, spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: piccalilli
directions: Chop the cabbage, tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Mix with the salt and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and press to remove all liquid possible.
Boil vinegar, water, sugar and spices 5 minutes.
Add the chopped vegetable mixture.
Bring to a boil and pour into sterilized jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: gizzard casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, stirring occasionally, or until gizzards are tender.
Or use a crock-pot, reducing water to 1 cup and cooking on low for 9 hours.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Yield: 3 quarts.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in large pan and add Worcestershire sauce.
Mix cereals and seasonings and add to pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray a 6-cup shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut the Cheddar-flavor cheese and the Mozzarella into 1/4-inch cubes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water, enough to dissolve it, for a few minutes.
In mixing bowl, combine oil, brown sugar and salt and add milk.
Stir until cool.
Add egg.
Add about 2 1/2 cups flour and mix well.
Add flour until dough makes a soft mixture.
Turn onto floured surface.
Cover with greased foil and let rest 10 minutes; knead about 2 to 3 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and cover with foil and cloth.
Keep in refrigerator overnight; roll out dough to about 1/2-inch.
Cut into squares and dip in melted butter and put in pan in layers.
Let rise about 3 hours until double in size.
Cook in oven at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Heat 1 stick margarine and pour over when it comes out of oven.

title: lemon cream cheese cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 2 baking dishes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine broth, celery and onion; cook until tender.
Combine chicken, broth mixture, mayonnaise, lemon juice, soup, eggs, 3/4 cup cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients and mix well; add to the first mixture and beat 1 minute.
Pour into 9-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add tomato soup and cook 15 minutes until thickened.
Stir frequently.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Add egg and milk to the macaroni.
Spread macaroni mixture in greased jelly roll or cookie pan.
Spread tomato beef mixture on top of macaroni.
Place thin slices of cheese on top and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: piggy wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles; cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Flatten a little or cut corn twists strips into 48 pieces to fit the sausages.
Flatten a little.
Bake until brown.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Lastly, add zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden lamb's sauerkraut balls
directions: Grind ham and pork together and saute until brown.
Add flour, milk and dry mustard and cook until thick.
Cook sauerkraut separately.
Grind the sauerkraut and meat mixture together. Return to stove and cook until thick.
Cool.
Shape.
Roll in flour.
Dip in milk.
Roll in cracker or bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat at 350° until brown.

title: alexandra's favorite drumsticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in bowl.
Dip drumsticks
in margarine.
Roll in flour mixture to coat.
Arrange in ungreased square pan and bake, uncovered, until done, about 50 minutes.

title: zucchini and cheese bake
directions: In a large skillet, put in a couple of tablespoons olive oil and saute garlic, onions, tomatoes and green pepper.
Saute until pepper is tender and tomatoes are mushy.
Set aside.
Saute zucchini in some more olive oil.
Cook until zucchini is 1/2 done, just tender.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix vegetables together with zucchini and put in a large glass or Corning pie or quiche dish. Cover with 2 cups of cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese, well drained.
Add mayonnaise and salt.
Grind or grate vegetables and drain them well.
Add to jello and cheese mixture.
Let set several hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: sticky rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Put frozen roll dough in the bottom of pan. Melt margarine. Add brown sugar and pudding. Stir and pour over frozen rolls. Let rise overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn Bundt pan over onto a large platter and rolls will pop right out. Enjoy!

title: copper carrots glaze
directions: Heat liquid to boiling.
Let stand overnight.

title: driskill hotel's cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots, celery and onion in butter.
Add flour and cornstarch.
Put vegetables in top half of double boiler.
Add milk and chicken stock.
Heat.
Add soda and cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted. Add seasonings.
Serve hot, topped with paprika.

title: easy cream pie
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Gradually add milk and Milnot. Cook on very low heat until thick. Add butter.
Pour in baked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Rub flour, shortening, sugar and salt to fine crumbs, saving 1/2 cup crumbs to sprinkle on top. Add baking powder, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, sour milk and eggs to batter. Mix well. Bake in a square cake pan. Sprinkle crumbs on top before baking. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty grilled potatoes
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onions to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among 3 large pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Seal each and place on grill approximately 30 to 45 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Makes 3 large servings.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Mix in saucepan and keep covered first 3 minutes, then cook to 242° on thermometer.
Beat 1/3 cup or 3 egg whites until stiff, while syrup is cooking.
Pour syrup slowly over whites and add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine, together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tunnel of fudge
directions: Cream butter in large bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and nuts until well-blended.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add 2 cans mild enchilada sauce and 1 can cream of mushroom soup to hamburger.
Spoon a small amount of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Layer 6 corn tortillas, 1/2 mixture, Cheddar cheese.
Repeat this with shells with remainder of mixture and finish with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: donald's honey chicken
directions: Season chicken. Bake or fry your chicken. Cover with honey and cook for 5 minutes.

title: lettuce salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients (not lettuce); mix well.
Spread over lettuce.

title: good vegetable salad
directions: Prepare marinade by stirring together salt, oil, sugar, water, vinegar and paprika.
Pour marinade over other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate
overnight.
Drain
1 hour before serving.

title: friendship bread
directions: Do not use metal spoons or bowls for mixing.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.
Serve with carrots, cauliflower, bell pepper, radishes, celery and tiny green onions.

title: sure-jell strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar thoroughly; set aside 10 minutes. Stir Sure-Jell with water in pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir mixtures together until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy. Pour into plastic containers.
Cover.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Store in freezer.

title: creamed corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook slowly about 30 minutes.

title: royal chocolate sauce
directions: Combine cornstarch, cocoa, margarine, honey and water in a heavy saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow creme and vanilla.
Stir until blended. Serve warm over ice cream or as a dip for fresh fruit and cake cubes. Makes 2 cups.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper in screw-top jar or small bowl.
Shake or whip with wire whisk until ingredients are well blended and of a thick and creamy consistency.
Use as dressing for fish, salads, hot or cold vegetables and for marinating meats.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, and eggs together and then all other ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cook for about 35 to 40 minutes.
The trick to a good carrot cake is to not overcook.
Frost when cool.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl, beat at medium speed until blended.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, set aside.
Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Gradually add sifted powdered sugar, beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Pour cream cheese mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.
Let cool completely in pan or wire rack.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.

title: marshmallow fudge bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows.
Spread on a 10 x 15-inch greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven; cover with marshmallows.
Return to oven for 3 minutes, or until marshmallows are soft.
Cool.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook well carrots; drain.
Mash.
Add salt and pepper, lots of butter, onion, green pepper and sharp cheese.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix all together.
Top with 1/2 Pepperidge bread stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Pour juice into percolator.
Put rest of ingredients into the basket of percolator.
Perk as if making coffee.
Recipe can be halved or doubled.

title: chicken relleno(stuffed chicken)
directions: Debone chicken where only skin, drumstick and wings are left. Ground chicken meat.
Mix chicken meat and all ingredients, except boiled chicken and Vienna sausages.
Spoon the mixture into the chicken skin.
Spread it flat and alternately arrange quartered, boiled eggs and Vienna sausage.
When done, spoon in the other half of the mixture.
Close the skin with toothpick.
Steam chicken for 3 hours.
Serves 20 people.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain off water.
Mix in all the ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°, then take 1/2 a package Pepperidge Farm dressing and 2 tablespoons margarine, melted.
Mix together.
Pour over top and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in double boiler; add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar and gradually pour hot mixture over this, while stirring.
Return to double boiler and cook 5 minutes longer.
Just before removing from heat, add lemon juice and rind.
Mix well.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: juanita's cocktail chicken balls
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed except 3/4 cup pecans. Mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in chopped pecans. Keep refrigerated until serving time.
These can also be frozen for later use.
Try spearing a chicken ball and a pineapple chunk on an hors d'oeuvre pick.

title: cream cheese peach pie
directions: Beat crust ingredients 2 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Stir spices into rice on bottom of casserole.
Top with browned pork chops.
Add consomme Top chops with sliced onion, tomato and bell pepper.
Bake covered 350° for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.

title: pineapple orange salad
directions: Place pineapple in saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in buttermilk and nuts.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour in dish.
Chill.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add all others.
Pour into buttered pan. Bake at 350° until firm.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: strawberry or peach pizza
directions: Grease a pizza pan.
Press the cookie dough in the pan, put pecans on top and press them down into the dough.
Bake 350 degrees for 10-15 minutes.
Cool.

title: norma's breakfast casserole
directions: In a well-buttered, 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, beginning and ending with cheese, layer cheese and chiles.
Mix eggs with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Pour egg mixture over layered cheese and chiles.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together the ingredients and pour over oleo (melted) in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: squirrel with rice
directions: Dice salt pork; saute until brown.
Add squirrel pieces; brown lightly.
Add water.
Simmer until tender.
Add rice, catsup, onion and seasonings.
Cook over low heat.
Cook until rice is tender.

title: lemon chess pie(a dessert of early virginia)
directions: Beat the eggs with a fork or wire whisk and gradually add the sugar.
Add the lemon juice and rind; mix well.
Slowly add all ingredients until completely blended.
Pour into an 8-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown or until a knife inserted into the filling comes out clean.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Stir together the 1 1/2 cups flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine nuts, brown sugar, 1 Tbsp. flour, butter and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 375 for about 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
In separate bowl, sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Pour batter into loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: apricot-filled pear cake
directions: Drain pears.
Save 1/2 cup juice.
Blend pears in blender until smooth.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, pureed pears, 1/2 cup pear juice and eggs at slow speed until smooth and moistened. Beat 2 minutes on high.
Pour batter in a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Grease a piece of wax paper and fit in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes, remove from pan and cool completely. Slice cake in half, spread apricot jam over cut half.
Replace top cake layer.
Spread with topping.
Chill well.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix in bowl pared and sliced apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix in another bowl flour, baking powder, salt, oil, orange juice, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/2 batter in ungreased Bundt pan.
Spread 1/2 the apple mixture.
Add remaining batter and top with remaining apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes before removing.

title: budapest tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a large Bundt pan and set aside.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, cocoa, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream together margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, mixing to blend.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to the large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Add sour cream and mix to blend.
By hand, fold in brown sugar-nut mixture.
Pour batter into prepared Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until done.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Alternate with flour and milk.
Add spices to flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken fillet casserole
directions: Beat eggs well and dip chicken in them, then dip chicken in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil and brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Put the chicken in a casserole dish.
Dissolve bouillon in a cup of hot water and add reserved mushroom liquid; stir well. Pour over the layered chicken and add the mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
At end of baking time, remove from oven and add enough slices of cheese to cover chicken.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: cocktail spread
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Then add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish to taste and spreading consistency.
Use any kind of crackers.

title: chili corn muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, chili powder and salt.
Chop scallion.
Beat milk, applesauce and egg until just combined and stir in scallion and corn.
Stir flour mixture into milk mixture until just combined but still lumpy.
Spoon into prepared muffin pans.
Bake until edges start to brown.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
They are great with chili and soups.

title: spider corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt shortening in frypan placed in oven.
Beat egg; add 1 cup milk.
Stir in cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Turn into frypan with melted shortening. Pour over remaining milk.
Do not stir.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: herman cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil with mixer.
Stir Herman, soda, salt, flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, raisins and 1/2 cup nuts or walnut flavoring together with a spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or two loaf pans.

title: baked brie with crudites
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons unsalted butter in a heavy medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Place Brie and cream cheese (cut in large pieces) in a large microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on Medium just until melted, about 2 minutes.
Whisk in onion mixture, sour cream, fresh lemon juice, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: In a Dutch oven over low heat, cook onions in butter until soft but not brown.
Add paprika and rub into onions with wooden spoon. Add chicken, meaty side down, and stock.
Bring to a boil, then cover and gently simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Chicken should be very tender and onions mushy.
Remove chicken to a platter and debone.
Cut larger pieces into serving chunks, if you wish.
Add 2 tablespoons of cooking liquid to cornstarch and mix well.
Add this mixture to liquid in pot.
Bring to a boil and stir until thickened.
Reduce heat and stir in sour cream, heating just to simmer point.
Add chicken, cover and simmer a few minutes until heated through.
Holds well at low heat.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Pour liquid into crumb mixture and mix with spoon.
Pour into greased oblong pan.
Place 1 cup crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peach tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and cream.
Pour the mixture over peach slices which have been arranged in the bottom of the pie shell.
Dot the top of the tart with butter. Bake for 10 minutes at 425°; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: meat and cheese tartlets
directions: Mix beef, seasoning mix and cold water. Shape in tartlet muffin pans, as mini-tartlet shell. Mix sour cream, taco sauce, olives and chips. Place one teaspoon of filling into each meat shell. Mound slightly. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 425°. Remove from pan. Serve immediately or freeze and reheat at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 30 tartlets.

title: wondrous brownie pie
directions: Beat until smooth or blend in blender until smooth. Pour into greased pie plate then pour nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: applesauce diabetic cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking soda.
In a large bowl mix margarine, sweetener and egg.
Mix in dry ingredients, alternating with applesauce.
Fold in raisins, cereal and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Lightly flatten with a fork dipped in milk.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: Stir salt in water until salt is dissolved; pour over cucumbers.
Let stand for one week; drain well.
Add alum; soak 24 hours in the alum water; drain well.
Split cucumbers; let them drain.
Wash churn; dry it.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach according to directions. Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter or oleo in saucepan over low heat. Add flour and stir until well blended, but not brown. Add onion and cook until soft and clear.
Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick. Continue stirring. Add seasoning and cheese which has been cut into small pieces.
Stir until melted. Combine spinach. Pour into casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken n' rice
directions: Spread
rice on bottom of small roasting pan.
Sprinkle mushrooms and pepper over rice.
Lay chicken pieces over this. Dilute
mushroom
soup
and
onion soup with water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered at 350° for 2 hours.

title: apple glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in large nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Add carrots and saute until carrots begin to brown slightly, about 8 minutes.
Add apple juice and honey and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until carrots are tender and liquid is reduced to glaze, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Transfer to bowl.
Sprinkle with green onion tops and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix for one minute in blender.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt, pepper and Schilling barbecue spice. Place ribs in broiler pan under broiler for 30 minutes to brown and remove excess fat.
Slice ribs into serving pieces and put in crock-pot.
Add onion and pour in barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, oil, eggs and lemon extract. Dissolve the jello in the hot water and add to the cake mix; mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
While hot, prick with toothpick and pour on frosting.

title: rum duff
directions: Combine applesauce, sugar, rum, grated orange rind and gingersnaps.
Stir until well mixed.
Chill.
Just before serving, fold in whipped cream and pile into sherbet dishes.
If desired, top with additional cream and nuts.

title: italian style bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain green beans, chick peas, Northern beans and pinto beans.
Add onion, bell pepper, red pepper, pimento, salt and pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Heat and stir until dissolved the vinegar, sugar and vegetable oil.
Mix together. Shake on wine vinegar and olive oil.
Garnish with purple onion rings.
Enjoy!

title: double-corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder, salt and red pepper.
In medium bowl, whisk milk, butter and egg.
Stir into dry ingredients just until combined.
Stir in corn.
Spoon into prepared pans.
Bake 20 minutes.
Unmold and serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole.
Cover with chicken.
Spread mushroom soup, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cajun hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, water, oleo and egg. Mix well.
Stir in onion and peppers.
Carefully drop batter by teaspoonful into hot oil.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown, turning once.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: 2 step chicken broccoli divan
directions: If using fresh broccoli, cut into spears.
In a 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole dish, arrange broccoli and top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.

Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or microwave by covering with wax paper and cooking on High for 6 minutes, or until hot, rotating dish halfway through heating.

title: pecan delight
directions: To prepare pan, line 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl. Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add oil mixture and blend well.
Add chopped pecans and apples.
Stir until well mixed. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour cake mixture into a large tube or Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O together.
Add boiling water; mix well. Add pineapple and orange juice.
Freeze in plastic 1 gallon container or 1 gallon Ziploc bag.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: french ice coffee
directions: Mix coffee and sugar together and cool.
Add half and half, milk and vanilla. Pour into Ziploc bags or milk cartons and freeze.
Two hours before serving, remove from freezer.
Serve with spoons at a slushy consistency.

title: pinto beans(german style)
directions: Wash beans.
Cover beans with plenty of water and bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes, set off burner, cover beans and let set for 1 hour.
Drain off water and rinse beans.
Cover with water and cook beans until tender.
Add onion and all other ingredients. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine meat,
onion soup mix, eggs, tomato sauce, bread crumbs, water and chopped pepper.
Shape into loaf and place in baking pan.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta to desired state; drain.
Dice green pepper and onion; add to pasta.
Add cooked and drained sausage.
Microwave pepperoni on a few paper towels for 2 to 3 minutes; pat oil off, then add to pasta.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Add hash brown potatoes (slightly thawed by rinsing with water in colander). Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle with onions. Mix together soup, sour cream and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan and mix in bread cubes.
Spoon over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding according to package and cool.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip until creamy.
Layer graham crackers and pudding mixture, keep layering until graham crackers are on top.
Top with icing and chill.

title: crescents
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Add 1/2 cup powdered sugar; beat well.
Combine flour and salt; gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Divide dough into fourths; cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Work with 1 portion of dough at a time, storing remainder in refrigerator.
Divide each portion into 12 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a 2 1/2 inch log; curve ends of each log to form a crescent.
Place crescents 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheets 1 minute.
Carefully roll warm cookies in 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar; cool completely on a wire rack.
Roll cooled cookies in remaining 1 cup powdered sugar. Store up to 1 week in an airtight container.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 425° or until golden brown.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/4 cup stuffing mix on top and dot with 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: golden apple pie
directions: Peel apples; core and slice thinly to measure 7 cups.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding. Pour whipped cream (8 ounces) in pudding.
Whip mixture.
Put cream cheese in mixture.
Mix mixture and whip.

title: the best and easiest peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Press each ball with fork.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or just until cookies start to turn brown.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Thoroughly
cream shortening, sugars and
vanilla.
Add	eggs and beat well.
Stir in peanut butter. Sift
dry
ingredients and stir into creamed mixture. Form	into tiny
balls
and
place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Dough may also be rolled and cut, if desired.
Bake 10 minutes.	Makes 8 dozen.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli spears on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Lay chicken pieces on top.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May also top with potato chip crumbs or buttered bread crumbs.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts and put in baking dish.
Puree apricots in blender and add lemon juice.
Pour mixture evenly over chicken. Sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Heat Marsala and butter in saucepan until butter is melted.
Pour over chicken.
Place under broiler approximately 30 minutes until glaze is brown. Serve with rice or rice pilaf and green veggie.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.
Yield: one 10-inch cake.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple thoroughly.
Heat juice in saucepan and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into bowl and add Coke.
Place in fridge until it begins to jell.
Add halved cherries, pineapple, pecan pieces and cream cheese chunks.
Combine and place back in fridge until firm.

title: graham cracker shells
directions: Grind graham crackers and empty into plastic bowl.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Mix with both hands until well mixed and all the mixture is moist.
Measure out 1 1/3 cups of mixture into each pie pan.
Use fork to line side of pan with mixture.
Spread remainder of mixture around bottom of pan and press down with bottom of flat glass.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Warm pie crust in oven about 10 minutes while the oven heats.
Shred cheese and place in mixing bowl. Crumble bacon into bits and add to bowl.
Whip eggs with fork and add to mixture.
Add milk, chives, salt and pepper to cheese mixture.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle surface with nutmeg.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving. Makes one (9-inch) pie.

title: pork chop and rice casserole (or chicken)
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
Cook in a little shortening until brown. Put in 2-quart or larger baking dish.
Brown pepper, celery and onion.
Put in dish with meat.
Add rice on top, then tomatoes. Bake in 350° oven until tender, about 45 minutes.
Might have to add 1/2 cup water when gets dry.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix oil, eggs and sugar.
In separate bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts. Spread into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Distribute chips onto top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
For best results, bake at least 2 to 3 days before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix (except onion and bacon) and put in baking casserole. Slice onion and put on top.
Put chopped bacon on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 400° to cook bacon and onion.
Reduce heat to 275° and bake, covered, for 2 to 3 hours more.

title: blend of the bayou
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter.
Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons butter and add to first mixture.
Add soup, mushrooms, seasonings, crab meat and rice.
Mix well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish and top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly. Serves 8 and leftovers freeze well.

title: cider stew
directions: To cut roast into 1-inch cubes, first trim excess fat from roast. Cut roast into 1-inch slices. Cut each slice in half lengthwise, then cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: golden coconut balls
directions: Spread coconut in a large shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes, until golden brown.
Turn into a small pie pan. Cool.

title: parmesan baked tomatoes
directions: Cube tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Spread tomatoes evenly in a casserole dish.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Sprinkle bread crumbs over tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese next.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade oreo ice cream
directions: Coarsely crush Oreo cookies to equal one cup. In a large bowl, beat egg yolks, stir in condensed milk and vanilla. Fold in cookies and whipping cream. Pour into an aluminum foil lined 9 x 5 inch loaf pan or other 2 quart container. Cover, freeze 6 hours or until firm. Scoop ice cream from pan or peel off foil and slice. Store in freezer.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crush garlic with salt in small bowl.
Add crumbled cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, paprika and pepper; stir until ingredients are well blended and dressing is smooth and creamy.
Chill.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: oven-fried catfish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well; set aside. Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and hot sauce, stirring well. Brush mayonnaise mixture evenly over both sides of fillets; dredge in cereal mixture. Place fillets in 9 x 13-inch glass cooking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 450° for 18 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges. Makes 8 servings.

title: sour cream pumpkin coffeecake
directions: Cream butter, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl.
Add 3 eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add dry ingredients to butter mixture alternately with sour cream.
Combine pumpkin, beaten egg, 1/3 cup sugar and pie spice. Spoon half of batter into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread to corners.
Sprinkle half of Streusel over batter.
Spread pumpkin mixture over Streusel.
Carefully spread remaining batter over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle remaining Streusel over top.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and garlic in butter in a large saucepan.
Add flour and seasonings and blend.
Gradually add stock and cook until thickened.
Stir in turkey, mushrooms and cheese.
Fold in cooked spaghetti noodles.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; top with crumbs and bake 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken soup and milk; reserve half of the mixture.
Mix remaining soup, rice and 1/4 of the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on top. Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: favorite peach pie
directions: Peel and halve peaches.
Lay face down in unbaked pie shell.
Mix coffee cream, sugar, cinnamon and flour together.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until lightly brown.

title: cinnamon christmas ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Will be a dense dough.
Knead well and roll out to 1/8-inch dough.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Use a straw to cut out hole for ribbon.
Lay on a flat surface to dry for up to 7 days, flipping to allow for even drying.
Decorate with acrylic paints and glitter.
String ribbon through straw hole.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach and drain well.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients in any order.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 45 minutes. Cut into squares.
Makes a "hit" served cold at receptions. Serves approximately 35.

title: cal's delicious chili
directions: Fry meats, celery, garlic and onion.
Add other ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour and gradually add milk and some of the cheese to make cheese sauce.
May need to use more flour before milk is added or more milk.
Put cooked macaroni in baking dish; stir in cheese sauce mixture.
Add more cheese to taste.

title: famous pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk or water.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and flour.
Mix all ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Form pretzels; brush with slightly beaten egg or a little egg white with a few drops of water.
Sprinkle with coarse salt and bake at 425° for 15 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, evaporated milk, bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper together well.
Form balls.
Brown meat balls in small amount of oil.
Mix together hot water, bouillon cubes, mushroom soup and chicken soup and pour over browned meat balls. Bake in 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: mexican cheese dish(great! xxx)
directions: Grate 10 ounces sharp Cheddar cheese into a 9 x 13-inch buttered Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle 5 tablespoons of finely chopped jalapeno peppers on top.
Grate 8 to 10 ounces Monterey Jack cheese on top of peppers.
Press down.
Pour 6 to 7 beaten eggs onto cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° or until set and golden. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Melt butter or margarine.
Mix with pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Place pie crust into pyrex pie plate and cook as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix instant chocolate pudding as directed using 1 cup less milk for each box.

When well blended, pour into cooled pie shell. When pie filling is set, spread Cool Whip on top of filling, shave Hershey bar into curls. Sprinkle chocolate curls on top of Cool Whip topping--then sprinkle walnuts on top also.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Simmer ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken pieces and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Trim meat.
Cut in strips 1 1/2 x 1-inch.
Coat with flour.
Melt butter in heavy skillet. Brown meat on all sides.
Add onion and garlic.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add to meat.
Add liquid from mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Cover.
Simmer until meat is tender and sauce is thick (about 1 1/2 hours).
Add mushrooms. Just before serving, combine vinegar with evaporated milk and stir in.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Top with chopped parsley.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: cherry delight
directions: Pour cherry filling in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter next.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars, add egg and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time except pecans.
Mix until combined; stir in pecans.
Form into balls the size of walnuts; place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown; do not overcook. Allow to cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water and ice cubes.
Cool until partially set.
Stir in all remaining ingredients and pour into molds; chill until set.
Makes 2 large jello molds.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Mix all in top of double boiler. Cook until thick and pour into a baked pie shell.

title: mexican cheese crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place crackers in large shallow baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine butter, taco seasoning mix, Worcestershire and salt.
Pour butter mixture over crackers; stir well.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 6 cups snack mix.

title: peanut butter parfait
directions: Mix Oreo cookies and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread ice cream on top of cookies.
Sprinkle on peanuts and freeze for several hours.
Melt chips and stir in sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread cooled fudge on peanuts and freeze.

title: blender banana bread
directions: Put egg, butter, bananas, sugar and granola into blender. Whirl on low until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add blender mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Yields one loaf.

title: colwell's special squash
directions: Cover squash and onion with water and butter and bring to boil.
Cook approximately 5 minutes, until tender.
Drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over squash. Makes 4 servings.

title: best ever deer and gravy
directions: Flour deer after salting and
peppering.
Fry
in oil to brown.
Meanwhile place a large
skillet
or
pot
on
another burner.
Depending on amount you
cook,
put water in pot.
For one package of deer to feed 4, use about 2 cups of water.
When meat is browned, drop directly
into
water
that is simmering. Do not drain on paper.
Continue
until
all
meat
is browned. Cook onions in oil until tender.
Drain off most of oil.
Brown small amount of flour and brown.
Add
all
this to water.
Add soup. Simmer, adding water if necessary.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a greased floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Spread icing on hot cake.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Shape into small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mother in law cake
directions: In
large
mixing
bowl
stir together dry ingredients. Make well
in
center;
drain pineapple, pressing out liquid. Reserve 1/3 cup syrup.
Add remaining ingredients.	Beat with wooden spoon.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, greased. Sprinkle with walnuts and brown sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve cold.
Keep refrigerated.

title: punch
directions: Add water as directed on lemonade. Mix together and serve.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, oil, dill weed and garlic.
Pour over oyster crackers; stir to coat.
Place in warm oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Store in tight container.

title: crispy crunchy brittle
directions: Place walnuts in 9-inch glass pie plate.
Microwave at High 5 minutes, stirring halfway through until toasted; set aside.
In 2-quart glass measuring cup with handle, combine sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt.
Microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring well at least once until sugar dissolves.
Microwave at High 4 1/2 to 7 minutes, stirring once after 2 minutes until mixture reaches 300°.
Stir in baking soda; add toasted walnuts. Turn at once into buttered 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread thin.
Let stand until cooled.
Break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll in balls the size of a small walnut.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Press with the bottom of a glass, dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle sugar generously on top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes. Makes 100 cookies.

title: green pepper pineapple salad
directions: Soak gelatin in the pineapple juice and dissolve over hot water.
Add to pineapple and cream cheese mixture.
Fill green peppers and set in refrigerator to harden.
With a very sharp knife, cut the stuffed peppers crosswise into thin slices.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Remove foil from Kisses.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour; blend until smooth. Stir in chips. Mold scant tablespoon of dough around each Kiss, covering completely.
Shape into ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.
Drizzle topping over each cookie (optional).

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix; put in loaf pan.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 300°. Serve warm.

title: chocolate chip butter cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add salt, vanilla and flour. Mix until blended. Mixture will be stiff. Stir in chocolate chips. Roll into balls (3/4 inch) and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° about 12 to 13 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creamy honey butter
directions: Beat butter until creamy and light. Add honey and orange extract and beat until fluffy. Taste at this point. If you like it sweeter, add a little more honey. Refrigerate.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Do not overmix.
Drop in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° until brown, approximately 20 minutes.
An especially good recipe for weight watchers.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
one
cup
hot
water and pineapple juice. Melt
cranberry
sauce
in
saucepan on low heat until smooth and
mushy.
Mix
with all other ingredients and chill until thickened
and then add diced apple.
Spoon into 8-inch square dish,
sprayed with Pam or salad oil for easy removal. Chill until
firm.
Cut
in squares and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise or Cool Whip.
Serves 8.

title: black bean lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Mash beans; stir in tomatoes, onion, peppers, salsa, chili powder and cumin. In a small bowl, mix ricotta cheese, garlic powder and egg. Spread 1 cup tomato mixture over bottom of dish. Top with 1/2 of noodles, overlapping a bit. Top with half of the remaining tomato mixture. Spoon ricotta cheese mixture over top and spread. Top with 1/2 of shredded cheese. Top with remaining noodles. Top with remaining tomato mixture. Sprinkle remaining shredded cheese on top. Cover with spray-coated foil. Bake about 45 minutes. Let stand about 15 minutes before serving.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix together thoroughly.
Add egg whites which are beaten.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and form in balls; put in Pyrex pan close together.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: In blender, mix Jell-O and water.
Add juice, vinegar and milk.
Add cream cheese, one piece at a time.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Pour in 2-quart mold and chill.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt oleo, add brown sugar and pretzels.
Spread in a 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake in 350 degree oven until bubbly (3-5 minutes). Combine cream cheese and white sugar, beat smooth.
Add in 1/2 cool whip, mix.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 c. boiling water, add strawberries.
Mix well, cool.
Pour over cream cheese layer and chill.
Top with remaining cool whip.

title: white monkey
directions: Melt margarine over low heat; stir in flour and cook for one minute.
Slowly add milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve over toast.

title: flank steak fix-up
directions: Rub steak with garlic; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Cut meat crosswise into 4 to 6 serving pieces.
In large skillet, cook bacon.
Drain bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Place slice of bacon on each piece of meat, roll up and secure with wooden picks.
Coat rolls with flour.
Brown rolls in the reserved bacon drippings over medium heat.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk in a large bowl.
Refrigerate one hour.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Then refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in refrigerator.
You can also freeze it.
I usually do this.
I divide it into 8 x 8-inch glass dishes.

title: diabetic persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, sweetener and egg.
Add dry ingredients and a little of the milk.
Blend well.
Add rest of milk and butter.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Chop chocolate coarsely.
Combine with oleo or butter and boiling water in a large saucepan.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted.
Add sugar and corn syrup. Heat slowly to boiling, lower heat and simmer gently 8 minutes. Watch carefully but do not stir.
Test for thickness on ice cube. Add vanilla.
Refrigerate leftover sauce in screw top jar.
Reheat in warm water (in jar) until soft enough to pour.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook the beef until browned, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat. Stir in soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Heat through,
stirring occasionally. Serve on buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large pot.
Boil it on the stove until the mixture becomes thick and the egg yolks have evaporated and there is no lumps.
Let this mixture cool for approximately 30 minutes.
Put mixture into a ice cream maker until it freezes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and then drain.
Pour ground beef in pan (8 x 10-inch).
Stir tomato soup in with the ground beef.
Pour green beans (drained) and then mashed potatoes until it covers the ground beef.
Pour shredded cheese over it.
Heat oven to 350° until cheese melts.

title: old fashioned spice cake
directions: Mix baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and olive spice in small bowl; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl; pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg, cloves and olive spice over top of cake.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel and mash avocado in bowl with lemon juice and salt. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise with taco seasoning in another bowl.
(I use 1/2 of the package of taco seasoning in the sour cream mixture and 1/2 in the refried beans.)

title: zucchini cake squares
directions: Blend together.
Cut like pie dough.
Press 1/2 on bottom of lightly greased pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes (on bottom rack).

title: polish noodles and cabbage
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add cabbage to skillet.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.

title: zesty grilled pork chops
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Place chops in a glass baking dish and pour marinade over.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 6 hours or overnight.
To cook, remove chops from marinade and grill or broil 4-inches from the heat to desired doneness. Brush occasionally with the marinade.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and baking soda.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in shortening until mixture resembles course crumbs; stir in raisins.
Stirring with fork, add buttermilk until mixture leaves sides of bowl and soft dough forms.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead lightly until no longer sticky.
Roll out 1/2
inch thick and cut with floured 2 1/2 inch cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet with sides touching.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes on wire rack and frost. Serve immediately.

title: savory italian rice bake
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni mix as package directs.
Remove sausage from casing and crumble.
In 12-inch skillet, brown sausage and onion; drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.
Set aside.
Add zucchini and garlic; saute over medium-high heat 1 minute.
Cover, continue cooking over low heat about 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Combine prepared Rice-A-Roni, sausage mixture, 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce and basil; spread into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cherry salad
directions: Heat 2 cups of water to boiling, pour over jello in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix in cherry pie filling and the crushed pineapple.
Let this mixture jell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pick meat from chicken (no skin).
Mix all ingredients, then tear up the bread like for dressing.
Stir all together.
Add enough broth to make all real moist, a cup or more if needed. Pour in large casserole dish or pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef vegetable stew
directions: Add meat, onion, celery and salt to 6 to 7 quarts boiling water.
