Boil on medium about one hour.
Add potatoes, carrots, bouillon and hot pepper to taste.
When beef is well done, add tomatoes. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: tossed fruit salad
directions: To make dressing, combine sugar, vinegar and water in saucepan.
Heat and stir just until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Stir in celery salt, paprika and mustard.
Add oil in slow stream, beating with electric mixer until thick.
Cover and chill.
Peel and section orange and grapefruit, reserving juices.
Peel and slice banana.
Brush with reserved citrus juices.
Set aside.
In large salad bowl, combine lettuce and escarole.
Arrange orange, grapefruit, banana, avocado and grapes in circle atop lettuce. Pour on chilled dressing.
Toss to coat fruit and vegetables. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Just before serving, add bacon or bacon bits.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Can be made the day before needed.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Shred cabbage (food processor or hand grater) and put into pot with 2 quarts water or broth.
Add the remaining ingredients after the cabbage shrinks down enough to make room for the rest.
Boil on medium-low for a few hours.
Yum!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add broccoli and onion.
Cook until broccoli is thawed.
Cut cheese into 1 square.
Mix cheese, soup, milk and rice in large bowl.
Add broccoli.
Mix and bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and rice is done.

title: fey family fruit cups
directions: Choose from the fruits, selecting
a
total
of
6 to 7 cups of fruit.
Mix
fruits, sugar lightly and coconut.
Chill covered. Just before serving, pour liquor or juice over fruit for extra pick up.
Serve in a beautiful bowl.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Add crunched chips and Tabasco; mix together.
Mix other ingredients in bowl; let meat cool and mix with salad.

title: molasses pecan cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, egg and molasses until mixture is smooth.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in chopped pecans.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cover the cabbage with 1-quart boiling water.
Add the salt; boil 5 minutes, drain dry.
In the melted oleo, add flour and stir well.
Add milk and cook until thickens a little.
Put cabbage in baking dish.
Add cheese to sauce and stir until melted.
Pour over the cabbage and cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in two 13 x 9-inch pans for 20 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, mix in large bowl 1 cup Pet milk and 1 cup sugar.
Bring to rapid boil and remove from heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add coconut.
Pour over hot cakes; cover completely.
In a saucepan heat to a rapid boil 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup Pet milk and margarine.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Pour over cakes to completely cover.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut if desired.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage and onion together until cabbage is almost done. Cook noodles; drain.
Mix noodles with cabbage, onion and sour cream.
Mix half of the cheese into mixture.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and then with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken-n-yogurt
directions: Dip chicken breasts in yogurt.
Roll in mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place in baking dish.
Place tinfoil lightly over dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in lime water for 24 hours, stirring often.
Rinse in cold water until cucumbers are lime free.
Water will be clear.
Combine cucumbers and onions in salted water.
Let stand for 3 hours and then drain.
In a large kettle, combine vinegar and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and heat to simmering.
Avoid boiling the vegetables for this will make them soft.
Pack while hot in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: oven-baked french toast
directions: Spray 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Cut bread into 1-inch-thick slices; arrange closely in single layer in prepared pan.
In large bowl beat eggs, whisk in milk, 3 Tbsp. of sugar, vanilla and salt; pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or over night.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Sprinkle bread with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Slice strawberries place in bowl.
Add lemon zest, juice, and remaining 1 Tbsp. sugar, mix lightly.
Serve over warm French toast.
Yields:
8 servings.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Spray pot with Pam. Combine all ingredients. Stir once. Cook on low 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla in small mixer bowl until blended. Add cocoa alternately with milk, beating until smooth. Fold in topping until combined. Spoon into pie shell and chill until firm or freeze.

title: pudding mix
directions: Store dry ingredients in airtight container.
For pudding, combine 1 cup mix with milk in pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Yields 9 batches (4 servings per batch).

title: pasta with vegetables and goat cheese
directions: Combine broth, wine, shallots and black pepper in large saucepan.

Bring to a boil, add broccoli, breaking florets apart. Add squash and mushrooms, reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add cream cheese, goat cheese and lemon juice, cook on low heat, stirring constantly until cheeses are melted.
Set aside, keeping warm.
Cook pasta according to package directions, drain.
Place in large serving bowl, add vegetable/cheese mixture, toss gently. Garnish with red pepper strips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coq au vin
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Reserve remaining flour. Saute chicken in 3 tablespoons of butter to brown.
Transfer to a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients and add to butter mixture; mix well.
Add eggs, bananas and pecans. Add 1 tablespoon vanilla (optional).
Grease a loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: margaritas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients
in
a large pitcher.
Fill pitcher with ice and
water.
Serve immediately in salt-rimmed glasses.

title: dillicious pot roast
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings from pan.
Crumble bacon; set aside. Sprinkle both sides of beef with lemon pepper marinade.
Brown beef in bacon drippings.
Combine mushroom soup, dill pickle and Worcestershire sauce; pour over browned meat.
Cover; simmer for about 2 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Remove to warm platter.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Skim fat from gravy; serve with roast.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water for 8 to 10 minutes, until tender.
Drain well.
Combine onions, green pepper and carrots in large bowl.
Mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients in second bowl.
Pour over carrot mixture.
Marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: popcorn surprise squares
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows; add gumdrops, popcorn, M&M's and nutmeats.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Cut into squares.

title: easy brunch casserole
directions: Place croutons in greased 9 x 13-inch metal pan.
Put grated cheese over croutons.
Brown sausage and place on top of cheese. Beat eggs and mix with soup, mustard, milk and mushrooms.
Pour over sausage.
Bake, covered, with foil in 300°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.
This recipe may be prepared the night before and refrigerated.
Serves 10.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Season pork chops and brown.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and mix well.
Slowly add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Alternately place potatoes, onions, pork chops and cream sauce in greased casserole.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: michigan white chili
directions: *Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Cool. Cut into bite size pieces.

title: green pea salad
directions: Gently add all ingredients to peas.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: maple nut chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sift the first 5 ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Make a well; add Wesson oil, egg yolks, water and maple flavoring.
Beat until smooth with spoon or mixer on medium speed.

Add cream of tartar to egg whites in large mixing bowl. Beat until whites are very stiff, then pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten egg whites, gently folding with rubber scraper, just until blended.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 14-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn pan upside down on bottle until cold.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Add vanilla.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Place in pan; let cool.

title: cioppino
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, in 8-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over medium heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook onion, green pepper and garlic until tender, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add tomatoes and their liquid, wine, parsley, salt, basil, pepper and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and ginger together. Add to other ingredients. Serve on lettuce with muffins.
It's delicious.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan, in hot oil, brown roast on all sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook for 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover; cook for 45 minutes, or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth. Gradually stir into soup mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Garnish with fresh parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and granulated sugar together.
Heat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugars together.
Gradually add the rice and unbleached flour.
Mix with hands until smooth; do not overmix.
Press into baking pan or shortbread mold.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: polish cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and melted butter. Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remainder into a 9-inch spring-form pan or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, lining bottom and sides.

title: mom's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers very thin.
Salt overnight, covered with water.
Drain, then cook with remaining ingredients.
Let stand in hot vinegar for a few hours, then reheat and can.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add peanut butter (the kind with oil on top).
Mix again.
Add M&M's and chocolate chips, mix well; then add uncooked oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet.

title: pastitso-greek lasagna
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Melt 3/4 stick of butter until slightly burned.
Put in macaroni; mix with some Romano cheese.

title: lynn's meatballs
directions: Simmer for about (or at least) 1 hour.
Making 1 day before is better.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash peppers; remove tops.
Finely grind peppers and onions; drain.
In large saucepan, combine peppers and onions; cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
To pepper mixture add sugar, vinegar, salt, dill seed and 1/2 cup water.
Boil gently, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Pack into hot half pint jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
(Start timing when water returns to boiling.)
Makes 10 half pints.

title: all-in-one muffin
directions: Beat brown sugar, oil or applesauce, egg, milk and banana until well blended.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt all at once.
Fold in cereal, dates and nuts.
Spoon batter into paper-lined 4-inch muffin tins until 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: holiday dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, turn heat to simmer, add marshmallows and dissolve.
Add drained pineapple.
Cool.
Whip milk and cream cheese in large bowl, add cold jello mixture.
mix well.
Pour into greased mold and refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream in mold pattern if desired.

title: "bev's cocoa"
directions: Mix together cocoa and sugar.
Add dash of salt and the water. Bring to boil.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Remove from heat. Serves 8.

title: cinnamon chews
directions: Combine all ingredients but cereal and melt in top of double boiler.
Add cereal, mixing quickly.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill; cut in 1/2-inch squares.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Wrap individually in waxed paper.

title: french onion dip
directions: Mix well. Cover. Chill.

title: western hash
directions: Brown onions, bell pepper and beef in large skillet.
Add tomatoes, basil, rice, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with slices of American cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain. Combine all ingredients.
Mix together and cook on low until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: ballistic bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy blowing billions of bubbles.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in medium bowl using wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish, if desired.

title: green bean and turkey casserole
directions: Mix vegetable/seasoning packet from Stove top Dressing, with hot water, and margarine in large bowl until margarine is melted. Stir in stuffing crumbs just till moistened. Let stand 5 minutes. Mix turkey and green beans in 2 qt. casserole dish. Mix soup and milk in another bowl until smooth; pour over turkey mixture. Spoon stuffing evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 6 servings. Easy and delicious!

title: spiced peaches
directions: Combine the vinegar, the juice from the peaches, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil until reduced by about half.
Remove the spices.
Stick the cloves into the peach halves and pour the syrup over peaches.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: red velvet frosting
directions: Cook water and cornstarch (stirring constantly until thick). Remove from heat and let stand until cold.
Add sugar, vanilla and margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spread on cool cake.

title: champignons bordelaise mushrooms with a bordelaise garnish
directions: Rinse the
mushrooms
in cold water and drain well.
If the mushrooms are large, slice them or cut them in half.
In a heavy skillet, heat
the	oil.
When
the
oil is hot, add the mushrooms and
salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over high heat, shaking the skillet
and
stirring so that the mushrooms cook evenly until they
are quite brown and crisp.
They should be almost mahogany colored.
Pour
the mushrooms and cooking oil into strainer
or sieve to drain.
To skillet, add the butter. When
melted,	add mushrooms.	Sprinkle
quickly
with
bread crumbs, shallots and parsley.
Toss and serve.
Serves 4.

title: toffee refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix crackers and margarine.
Press 2/3 cup of cracker mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare pudding with 2 cups milk; add softened ice cream and blend until smooth.
Pour over crust. Put in the freezer until set.
Remove and spread Cool Whip on the top.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top and crushed Butterfinger bars.

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, egg and peas.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with potato chips, etc. and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 3 to 5 servings.

title: picnic cake(very rich)
directions: Mix dates in hot water.
Set aside.
Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with date mixture to egg mixture.
Mix well each time. Stir in vanilla and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sunrise cherry pie
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving two tablespoons syrup. Combine softened cream cheese, vanilla and reserved syrup, mixing until well blended.
Stir in 1/4 cup pineapple and 1/2 cup pie filling.
Gradually add sugar to cream, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold into creamed cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Top with remaining pineapple and pie filling.
Chill until firm.

title: peanutty chewy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly; add eggs.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top evenly with chips, then sweetened condensed milk and coconut.
Return to oven; bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: meat marinade
directions: Let chicken pieces or steak marinate in this mixture for 6 to 8 hours.
Excellent on the grill.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender or mixer.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and margarine.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives and pimento.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough up to center of mixture and seal.
Brush tops with melted margarine; dip in crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pork in a crock-pot
directions: Place in crock-pot.
Add dash of seasonings.
Pour mixed soup and water over chops.
Cover; let cook all day on low.

title: tuna 'n noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add drained tuna, soup, a little butter and some milk.
Peas may be added if desired.
Mix well.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Cream
sugar
and
shortening.	Beat in eggs.
Dissolve soda in	sour milk; add alternately with the flour and baking powder that
has
been sifted together. Stir in vanilla, nuts and	mashed bananas.
Drop
by
spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cream, 1 cup sugar and shortening. Add eggs; mix well.
Add apples, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist chewy chocolate cake
directions: Note:
Buttermilk can be replaced with 1/2 cup whole milk mixed with 1 tablespoon vinegar.

title: super nacho casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into baking dish.
Add the remaining ingredients in the order given.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Combine the milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water; add about 2/3 of the flour and beat thoroughly.
Let rise until double; add remaining flour.
Knead well.
Let rise again until double.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with a 3-inch biscuit cutter.
Brush rounds with melted butter.
Grease thoroughly center with dull edge of knife.
Fold double, pinch edges together and place on well-greased pan, one inch apart.
Allow to rise until double in size.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak the beans overnight; drain.
Add the water.
Add the cloves, bay leaf, garlic, celery, carrot and onion.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Mash beans.
Add the beef broth.
Combine the flour and melted butter; add to soup.
Add the sherry wine to taste. Adjust seasoning.
Serve with slice of lemon.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix dry cake mix, eggs and oil.
Add raisins, nuts or coconut. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix beaten eggs, sugar and syrup. Add melted butter, vanilla and chopped pecans. Pour into uncooked pie crust. Bake for 20 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. In mixing bowl, cream eggs, 2 sticks margarine (melted), powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer 15 minutes, no less.
Spread over crumbs.
Slice bananas thin, and layer pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot fudge for cake
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips together.
Add powdered sugar. Pour a little milk at a time.
Heat on stove.
Will not get real thick until after it cools.

title: southwestern skillet supper
directions: Heat oil in a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add beef and onion and cook until brown.
Stir in chili powder and salt.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn.
Cook over high heat until bubbling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Prepare potatoes as directed on package.
Stir in cheese and cilantro.
Top mixture with 1/2 cup of potatoes and enjoy.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Weigh 7 pounds pickles and put them in salt water that will float an egg.
Let them stand 3 days, then 4th day change to clear water for 3 days, changing the water daily.
Cut pickles in chunks, put them in weak vinegar.
Add a teaspoon of alum to every quart of water to cover them, and let them stand a day.
Make a syrup out of 3 parts water and 3 parts vinegar, 1 tablespoon each cinnamon, cloves and allspice, 1 teaspoon celery seed and 1 tablespoon mustard seed.
Put all spices in a thin cloth and boil it in your syrup for a while.
Then fill your cans and pour the syrup over them and seal cans.

title: cabbage and sausage
directions: Cut cabbage up like slaw. Set in bowl aside. Saute pan sausage. Drain grease from sausage. Add stewed tomatoes and let simmer for while. Add cabbage a little at a time. Then let all simmer until cabbage is cooked down. May add a cup or two of water if needed.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Spread crushed pretzels on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Melt margarine or butter with 2 tablespoons sugar and pour over pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store tightly covered.
To make tea, use about 2 teaspoons of mix per 1 cup hot water.
This drink is great in cold weather.

title: peel a pound soup
directions: May want to use tomato juice.

title: chicken-in-a-packet
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut four 20-inch long pieces of foil. Divide and layer tomatoes, onions, mushrooms, peppers and potatoes on each foil piece. Place chicken breast on top of vegetables. Mix Worcestershire sauce and pepper in a small bowl. Spoon over each breast. Top with 1 teaspoon margarine and 1 teaspoon honey. Seal packets by bringing opposite sides of foil together and fold over several times. Fold over the other two ends of foil tightly. Pierce top of foil twice with knife to vent. Arrange packets on baking sheet. Bake for about 35 minutes. Can be assembled ahead and refrigerated for up to two days. A great do-ahead main dish for a week-end bar-b-que. Can be grilled as well. Place foil side down about 4-6 inches from heat source for about 15 minutes. Serves four.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes a sticky dough.
Refrigerate one hour or overnight. Use a lot of flour to roll out.
Makes four 9-inch pies.

title: turkey bacon club sandwich
directions: Cut each roll lengthwise into 2 halves.
Spread mayonnaise on 1/2 of each roll.
Place 3 slices of cooked turkey bacon over the mayonnaise.
Place tomato slices and lettuce over the turkey bacon. Serve open-faced or as a closed sandwich.
Enjoy!!

title: best ham sandwiches
directions: Melt butter.
Add rest of ingredients; stir.
Brush top and bottom of bun.
Stack with ham and cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: red cake
directions: Mix vinegar and soda and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Add a little food coloring to cocoa to make a paste.
Add to creamed mixture with rest of coloring.
Add flour and salt, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla, then vinegar and soda.
Beat well.
Use 2 (8-inch) round pans (greased and floured).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
When cooked, split to make 4 layers.

title: batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Leave in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Fill muffin pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool. Add strawberries, pineapple, cranberry sauce and pecans. Put into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan or mold sprayed with cooking spray. Chill until firm.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Add salt and pepper to meat.
Toss all ingredients together and serve.
Leftovers taste good too, only not crunchy.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar; add eggs and mix.
Add buttermilk.
Add vanilla, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in flour until mixed well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop mixture by using a tablespoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.
May ice with lemon frosting.

title: quick microwaved streuseled apples
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in 8-inch glass dish.
Then mix last of ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over top of apples.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Can serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: just delicious cookie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Shape into balls on cookie sheet.
Dip a fork or glass in sugar and flatten each cookie. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: onion pork chops
directions: Place chops in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chops.
Add 1/4 cup water and bake in 425° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients and top with dressing.

title: banana freeze
directions: Combine sugar and water. Boil 3 minutes. Cool.
Mash bananas. Add to fruit juices and stir in sugar syrup.
Pour into containers and freeze. When ready to serve, thaw slightly.
Pour carbonated beverage over mixture.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Parboil cabbage to loosen leaves.
Mix meat, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Roll balls in cabbage leaves.
Place in pan and pour mixture of soup, sauce, vinegar and sugar over.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown meat, garlic, salt and pepper in margarine.
Drain and add tomato sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Soften cream cheese and add to sour cream and onions.
Combine meat mixture and noodles (or lasagna) and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: To make meatballs:
Combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft).
Shape into walnut size meatballs.
Place meatballs in a single layer on wax paper lined cookie sheets.
Freeze until solid.
Store frozen meatballs in freezer bags until ready to cook.
Makes approximately 80 meatballs.
These are good for something rather quick.
Takes approximately 1 hour baking time.

title: cough syrup
directions: Boil all ingredients, except honey, for about 3 minutes. Strain through cloth to remove all seeds and lemon rind.
Mix well with honey.
Take one warm tablespoon at a time at 1/2 hour intervals.

title: goulash
directions: In a skillet, brown beef in the vegetable oil.
When browned, add the flour and stir until flour starts to brown.
Add water and stir.
Add the hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Now add the carrots, onions, peppers and tomatoes if desired.
If the sauce seems too thin at this point, you can thicken it with a bit of rue which is flour that you have heated in just a slight bit of vegetable oil or you can add just a touch of cornstarch.
Once the vegetables have been added, bring to a boil once again, then cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
The longer it simmers the better it will taste.
It is great served over noodles or over rice.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until just firm.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add bread, sausage, etc. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: uncle joe allen's salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large bowl.
This is a great salad and easy to make.

title: barbecue sauce for meatballs
directions: Cook onion, celery and pepper.
Add ketchup, sugar and vinegar.
Warm, then add to meatballs.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Add onion, catsup and dressing into blender or food processor. Add softened cream cheese into mixture and blend until mixed. Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar and flour; whip eggs and add to juices. Cook until it thickens.
Add the macaroni and all the fruit to 3/4 container Cool Whip.
Cool 2 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Let cool, peel and mash.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter to potatoes.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly banana pudding
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk together.
Fix pudding by directions.
Mix milk mixture to pudding.
Make layer of bananas, wafers and pudding mixture or put pudding mixture on the bottom of 9 x 10-inch pan.
Put bananas and wafers in, then to finish, put a layer of Cool Whip on top.
Cool for 1 hour before serving.

title: chili rice
directions: Saute onion in oil in 2-quart boiler.
Add rice, salt and chili powder.
Pour in broth plus enough water to make 16 ounces liquid.
Bring to
boil and then cover and simmer until rice is done.

title: aunt janet's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery in skillet; drain fat.
Pour hamburger into baking dish, 2 1/2-quart dish.
Add 3 cups boiling water, rice and dry vegetable soup.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until juice is cooked up.

title: happy life recipe
directions: Take Love and Loyalty, mix it thoroughly with Faith.
Blend it with Tenderness, Kindness and Understanding.
Add Friendship and Hope, sprinkle abundantly with Laughter.
Bake it with sunshine.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with margarine.
Stir flour with salt and paprika and mix well.
Wrap 1 tablespoon of mix around each olive. Completely cover the olive.
Freeze in a plastic bag.
To serve, place frozen puffs on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until golden.
Olives will be quite hot. Serve on toothpicks.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together.
Add the strawberries.
Bake in 3 round cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool before frosting.

title: mixed fruit pies
directions: Mix
milk and lemon juice; add other ingredients.
Pour in crusts.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oil over low heat. Add garlic and parsley.
Remove from pot.
Brown chicken slowly in remaining oil.
Add bouillon, vegetables, rice, salt, cayenne pepper, Worcestershire and water.
Cook over low heat 1 hour.
Add sausage.
Add more water, if necessary, and correct salt.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cream the cream cheese with the sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Combine with the thawed topping.
Remove the brown crumbs from angel food cake.
Break or cut the cake into small pieces. Mix cake with the creamed mixture.
Combine cherry pie filling with almond flavoring.
Swirl into cake mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or serve from a pretty crystal bowl.

title: brownies #2
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add chocolate syrup, nuts and flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo, egg and vanilla.
Put into a greased
and
floured 9 x 13-inch metal pan.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar, eggs, pecans and vanilla.	Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: polk salad
directions: Gather polk greens in spring of year.
Look and wash well. Parboil greens; rinse.
Boil again.
Put 2 tablespoons of soda in water, rinse well.
Squeeze out all the water you can.
Put greens and cut up onion in skillet with fair amount of Crisco.
Cook until onion is translucent.
I like to scramble 3 or 4 eggs, then mix with cooked greens.

title: hidden valley ranch quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle cheese in pie crust.
Whisk eggs until frothy.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until center is set.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix.
Spread over mix.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: onion mushroom rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, bring to boiling soup mix, rice and water.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in green onions, if used.
Yields 4 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box; add poppy seed to cake mix. Stir and bake as directed.
Poke holes in cake and add in holes caramel syrup.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed up candy bars.

title: baneberry tarts
directions: Combine butter and sugar. Mix in egg yolks, flour, and vanilla. Roll balls the size of marbles. Indent with your thumb and fill with a dab of jelly. Bake at 350 for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Heat 3 to 4-inches of oil to 375° in deep fryer.
Measure 1 1/2 cups flour and the remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour. Turn dough onto well floured surface. Roll around lightly to coat with flour.
Gently roll dough 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter. With wide spatula, slide doughnuts into hot fryer. Turn doughnuts as they rise to surface. Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown. Carefully remove from oil.
Drain.
Serve plain, sugared or frosted. Makes 2 dozen.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all together.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.
Let cool, cut into squares.

title: baked creole eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplant; drain.
Saute onion, celery and shrimp in butter in skillet.
Add tomato.
Cook to desired consistency.
Add salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaf. Add eggplant.
Spoon into 4 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Place chicken parts in large saucepan with water to cover. Cook over medium-high until tender.
Remove from saucepan and dice meat, reserving cooking liquid.
Fry sausage.
Dice or chop.
In 2 teaspoons of sausage fat, saute chopped onion, pepper and celery until almost tender; then add scallion.
Cook few minutes more. Add ham, sausage, chopped chicken, butter and parsley to pan.
Add the reserved liquid from cooking to chicken; season with salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes before blending into rice.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Combine eggs, half and half and cheese.
Cook ham slice and cut into small cubes.
Add to mixture.
Add parsley and garlic powder. Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.
When done, middle should be raised and browned lightly. Cover pie crust edge with foil to keep from overbrowning.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Crush red hots to powder.
Mix to all other ingredients.
Keep in a closed container.
Add 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup boiling water.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter, sugar and pumpkin until smooth.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Sift flour, baking powder and spices together and add alternately with milk to egg batter.
Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon sugar on top before baking.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.
Do not open oven door while baking or muffins will have a tendency to fall. Equal amount of mashed sweet potatoes may be substituted for the pumpkin.
May be frozen and reheated.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini.
Roll in flour, then roll in milk/egg mixture. Roll in bread crumb/Bay seasoning mixture.
Let set 1 hour before frying in canola oil.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with lettuce and ending with bacon.

title: mini morsel cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar and vegetable oil.

Mix well. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually stir in flour mixture. Stir in mini morsels (do not use whole bag, it will be more than you need). Shape into balls. Roll in remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: beef stew - oven baked
directions: Put meat in roaster.
Add onion soup mix; sprinkle on.
Add potatoes, onions and carrots.
Mix together cream of celery soup, water and catsup.
Pour over stew.
Bake, covered, for 2 to 3 hours.

title: veggie dip
directions: Combine ingredients; serve with veggies.
Especially good with raw cauliflower.

title: strawberry cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Put in blender or food processor. Add cheese in 1-inch cubes.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in berries and nuts.
Pour into mold.
As jello begins to thicken, stir to distribute fruit and nuts evenly.

title: fried catfish
directions: Mix together flour, salt, pepper and other seasonings with corn meal.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: pralines
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring them to a boil.
Brown the 1/3 cup sugar; add to first mixture while cooking to soft ball stage.
Drop on oil paper.

title: rolls
directions: Add dry yeast to warm water.
Add sugar and egg to yeast and water; add Crisco and flour.
Mix until smooth.
Turn into large bowl.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Take out and knead lightly.
Pat out 1-inch thick and cut out.
Place on buttered pan and butter top.
Let rise at room temperature about 1 hour.
Bake at 500° for 12 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and 1 egg with orange flavoring and rind and set aside.
Cover apricots in warm water and soak for 30 minutes.
Drain apricots and cut them in small pieces.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Add water and juice.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice the meat diagonally against the grain into 1/8-inch strips.
Heat a large nonstick or regular skillet (use 1 tablespoon of oil) and brown the steak quickly over high heat. Push aside.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain and crumble into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Mix well the remaining ingredients; pour over sausage mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, until set and browned on top. Cool 5 minutes before slicing.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; chill.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.

title: orange sour cream cookie frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating well until spreading consistency.
Place 1/4 teaspoon frosting on each warm cookie.

title: hot island splash
directions: Combine both ingredients; heat until boiling.
Serve hot. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: austria viennese noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water until done.
Drain well. Saute onions, green pepper and celery in 1/4 cup butter.
Add to noodles with salt, pepper and parsley flakes; stir well.
Blend in sour cream and lemon juice.
Place in buttered casserole; top with crumbs, blended with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into hot cooking oil. Cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: jello-sour cream dessert
directions: Make jello using boiling water, add strawberries, bananas, and crushed pineapple. Put half mixture into a 9 inch square pan, chill until firm. Spread with the sour cream and add the rest of the jello mixture. Chill till firm. Cut into square to serve.

title: cream puffs(with cream filling)
directions: Combine butter or margarine, salt and water. Heat to boiling. Sift flour and measure. Add to boiling mixture. Beat vigorously until mixture leaves sides of saucepan and does not cling to spoon.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Meanwhile, grate the cheese, set aside.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper, swish lightly until smooth.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Butter 10 x 15 pan. Fill with graham crackers, broken apart. Bring to a boil butter and sugar and boil for 2 minutes. No more. Add pecans and pour over crackers. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Separate with fork and put on foil at once. Keep in Tupperware container in refrigerator. Keeps up to 2 to 3 weeks. Do not freeze.

title: brownies
directions: Mix as for drop cookies.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes or until done. Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: fancy franks
directions: Slice each hot dog in half lengthwise.
In small bowl, crumble onion rings.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for topping.
Combine potatoes, butter, crumbled onions, salt and pepper in shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and blend well.
Combine soup and milk in small bowl.
Pour 3/4 soup mixture over potato mixture and blend. Arrange hot dogs, cut side down, on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Pour remaining soup mixture over onions. Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: oriental salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Dice bacon and fry crisp.
Remove bacon from pan and lightly brown almonds in the bacon fat.
Drain on paper towels; blot excess fat away.
Combine sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, paprika, celery seed, honey, onion, mustard and salt in saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly and pour into a jar with tight lid.
Add oil and shake well.
Combine lettuce, oranges, bacon and almonds in serving bowl.
Pour warm dressing over salad just before serving.

title: quick trick fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a full boil.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and beat until thick.

title: sante fe style chicken breasts
directions: Cut avocado into large dice.
Combine with tomatoes, onion and cilantro.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons lime juice.
Add salt and pepper if desired.
Toss gently.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.
Melt butter in a skillet and saute the garlic.
Lightly brown chicken on each side, then remove to a plate.
To drippings in skillet, add marmalade, chili powder, salt, pepper and remaining lime juice.
Return chicken to skillet and coat with glaze.
Simmer until cooked through.
Serve with guacamole.

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden.
Separate into rings, if desired.
Add pepper rings and cook until tender.
Combine ingredients in a 2-quart shallow casserole and toss lightly. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill, and serve.

title: potato patties
directions: Add chopped onion to mashed potatoes.
Form into patties. Brush with butter.
Fry in butter greased frying pan until golden on each side.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain and set aside.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel and chili powder together.
Place Doritos in a casserole dish. Put meat and onion on top of that.
Pour mixture on top of meat. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter 4 to 5 minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop off on waxed paper to cool.

title: honey butter chicken
directions: Toss chicken in your favorite coating.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in roasting pan.
Roll chicken in butter.
Arrange in pan skin side down.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt 1/4 cup butter with honey and lemon juice.
Turn chicken skin side up and drizzle with honey mixture.
Bake another 30 to 40 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: biscotti di prato
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place almonds in shallow pan and bake until golden brown (8 to 10 minutes).
Let cool.
Reduce oven to 300°.
In small bowl, whisk together the eggs, vanilla and extract. In mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Add egg mixture and mix until blended, about 1 minute.
Cut almonds in half and mix in.
Divide dough in half.
On greased and floured baking sheet, pat out dough into 2 logs, about 1/2-inch high, 1 1/2-inches wide and 12-inches long, spacing them about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Transfer to wire rack.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: ground beef ragout(with pate grand-pere - dumplings)
directions: Cook beef in margarine.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Brown, stirring often.
Add other ingredients, mix, cover, and let simmer.
Prepare dumplings (pate grand-pere).

title: apple pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in hot fat.
Place apple slices in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with butter or margarine. Top with browned chops, Cover. Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: queso napolitano(cream cheese flan)
directions: Heat sugar in skillet over medium-high heat until melted, clear and light brown, stirring occasionally.
Spoon syrup over bottom and around sides of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef; cook macaroni.
Mix all but pizza sauce and mozzarella cheese together.
Place in a 9 x 13 pan, pour pizza sauce over the top, then sprinkle the mozzarella cheese over the pizza sauce.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil until the last 10 minutes.
A can of mushrooms can be added to the meat mixture if desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour gradually and mix well.
Chill dough.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until set, not brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: rosy glow punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice cocktail and concentrate.
Stir well; chill.
Just before serving, pour into a 4 quart punch bowl.
Add scoops of sherbet.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Makes about 50 (1/2 cup or 4 ounce) servings.

title: shells, cheese and tomato macaroni
directions: Cook shells for 14 minutes; drain.
Mix everything else together and add to drained shells.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut eggnog
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients.
Mix 1 cup into eggs.
Mix back into pan.
Stir over low heat 5 minutes to thicken.
Strain and chill.
Add nutmeg, if desired.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add cubes, garlic powder and pepper. Next, add onion, celery, carrots and cabbage.
Boil gently until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes; boil gently until all is heated and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: In greased baking dish or 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, peppers and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 8.
